Subject: Using Claude for your everyday life (4/5)
Body Text:
While Claude excels at work tasks, it can be just as valuable for your personal 
life, tackling everyday challenges and projects. Here's how Claude fits into 
your personal life.







Using Claude for your everyday life




Hi there,



 While Claude excels at work tasks, it can be just as valuable for your 
personal life, tackling everyday challenges and projects. Here's how Claude 
fits into your personal life:



1. Life assistant: Let Claude tackle recurring household planning tasks that 
eat up your time. Try: "I'm tired of meal-prepping the same 5 meals. Can you 
suggest some unconventional ideas that are easy to prepare but packed with 
protein?"



2. Personal learning coach: Claude can help you acquire new skills or 
knowledge more efficiently. Try: "I want to learn basic Spanish for my upcoming 
trip. Create a two-week study plan with daily 15-minute lessons."



3. Decision-making support: Facing complex personal choices? Claude can 
organize information and help you think through options. Try: "Help me compare 
Portugal and Switzerland for an upcoming vacation based on culture, cost, and 
travel logistics."



4. Creative project partner: Whether planning celebrations or pursuing 
hobbies, Claude can spark ideas and help with execution. Try: "I need creative 
ideas for my parents' 40th anniversary celebration that won't break the bank."



5. Simplify complex tasks: Need help understanding complex topics? Claude can 
break down technical, academic, or professional concepts into simple terms. 
Try: "Break down my car insurance policy so I understand what each section 
means."





Talk to Claude  <https://docs.anthropic.com/en/prompt-library/library>



With the Claude mobile app, personalized help is always at handwhether you're

Subject: Junior Data Analyst to Senior Pipeline
Body Text:
View this post on the web at https://jessramosdata.substack.com/p/junior-data-analyst-to-senior-pipeline-69d

Got BDE?
Junior Data Analyst to Senior Pipeline
So youve landed your dream data analytics role (or maybe just one that pays the bills), and youre wondering whats next. How can you grow your skills, get noticed, and more importantly make more money! (check out this Insta video  [ https://substack.com/redirect/952f4a1f-6314-44ff-aa40-4dd7d078d3be?j=eyJ1IjoiNTFkc2s3In0.TG_s5GaRal_EYLFDF-UYKHL5eEiDcX8TdL6-5nynlYA ] w/ my negotiation tips!)
Of course growing your skills is important, but playing the political game is what really matters for promos
The Difficulty of Jumping to Senior
Moving from a Junior data analyst position to Senior can be really tricky especially if you have to navigate red tape, politics, and seniority at your company. Especially at a bigger company with more policies and procedures around promos, it can be super difficult to move up unless youre getting your name out there and getting visibility with leadership. 
Sometimes they even have arbitrary rules about having to be in a position so long before getting promoted, yadda yadda yadda!!
Ive always worked in smaller startups (mostly), so its been easier for me to advocate for my work and make it visible, but Id be lying if I said it was easy to move to the senior level and that I didnt have imposter syndrome when I first got promoted up!
How I got Promoted to Senior
I got promoted to the senior level from a regular data analyst job completely because I advocated for myself and asked for a raise to better match my job duties. If you dont ask, you wont get it. I was doing a lot and fulfilling a lot of responsibility including managing someone, leading sales calls, and creating data insights for our execs to present to investors for a capital raise. 
Thats a LOT of responsibility for a data analyst only making $72K a year 
So I advocated for a higher salary just over $100K which was closer to an average data analyst salary in tech at the time. Unfortunately, they denied my raise request (dont worry, I got it the second time I advocated a year later), but they did give me my senior title. So kind of a win for my career even though titles dont pay my bills 
Having that senior title though gave me confidence when I grew into it and opened up other career opportunities for me because recruiters took me more seriously on the job market.
Self-Advocating & Visibility
My biggest advice is to self-advocate. You wont get what you dont ask for. Very rarely do people get promos they didnt ask for and set themselves up for. Passive is not the way to go! 
But it wont always work in your favor I NEVER got promoted OR got a raise in my last job of almost 2.5 years  
Sometimes politics, layoffs, budget, etc. can come into play and its completely out of your control. But its always worth trying! The first step you need to do is make your work visible and make sure stakeholders and leadership understand the full impact of your work.
This is how you can really stand out. It all starts with good stakeholder and leadership relationships + self-advocating and making your work impact visible!
Best of luck, and ALWAYS ask for more money and then add tax 
If youre new here:
 Who Am I?
Im Jess Ramos, the founder of Big Data Energy and the creator of the BEST SQL course and community: Big SQL Energy. Check me out on socials: LinkedIn [ https://substack.com/redirect/22e69f90-c4d9-44cb-b008-ca0d3a998f09?j=eyJ1IjoiNTFkc2s3In0.TG_s5GaRal_EYLFDF-UYKHL5eEiDcX8TdL6-5nynlYA ], Instagram [ https://substack.com/redirect/5361384d-6fca-478a-8263-a68ab22c6a0a?j=eyJ1IjoiNTFkc2s3In0.TG_s5GaRal_EYLFDF-UYKHL5eEiDcX8TdL6-5nynlYA ], YouTube [ https://substack.com/redirect/491fa091-0718-48a1-9192-9073e5ed11cd?j=eyJ1IjoiNTFkc2s3In0.TG_s5GaRal_EYLFDF-UYKHL5eEiDcX8TdL6-5nynlYA ], and TikTok [ https://substack.com/redirect/36c6724e-1cdb-47e0-b0ae-89c60f0619ad?j=eyJ1IjoiNTFkc2s3In0.TG_s5GaRal_EYLFDF-UYKHL5eEiDcX8TdL6-5nynlYA ]. And of course subscribe to my newsletter [ https://substack.com/redirect/2650f642-11b7-4baf-9ab8-6275a980e2f9?j=eyJ1IjoiNTFkc2s3In0.TG_s5GaRal_EYLFDF-UYKHL5eEiDcX8TdL6-5nynlYA ] here for all my upcoming lessons and updates all for free!

the growth zone and push our limits. How can we   
 in ourselves: .    
: Start by challenging yourself more. Seek out situations where you can

jobs out of your comfort zone. You'll make mistakes, but that's okay. Every
challenge you face is an opportunity to learn. .

Subject: Live today at 4:30 PM PST: How to Nail Your Technical Interviews at FAANG+
Body Text:
Learn how to handle difficult questions and unseen problems using our unique Power Patterns Methodology

Hi Candace,

Looking to break into Top Tech companies? Interview Kickstart's structured curriculum, focused practice, and personalized mentorship is your ticket to career growth.

Join our session today at 4:30 PM PST to discover your blueprint for FAANG+ interview success.

Seats Are Filling Up FastReserve YOURS Now!

How to Nail your next Technical Interview

 Friday, April 18 (today!) at 4:30 PM PST

 Register here for our today's webinar
(https://d1KhQf04.na1.hubspotlinks.com/Ctc/GF+113/d1KhQf04/VVXg9p7sqsdSW40kyP16MTcWJW2lg-cV5vxMb1N76MZ_n3gVDYW8wLKSR6lZ3nkW6lcN6m5gX1fSVYKdjH4Lb4SQW6j_1sl2-Lr4jW3-VRQK4DvzwNW49T7145J95R3W7dh9-q4zdSzwW5zbQ-d6vzjYQW26TCj02Zhb19W6LHwJh8_rrQ8W1ZF0k07NM14bW1SgdZX6ywMV7V-6pBT97y_HPW8VH0Jj6V8tcfW3WSwr94bXhYyW4YTv0r5GzbF0VdgWyB7dTtVXW5fl-Db1K0prkVyhynr87kbrfW1XDL_16C-JsVW5Q7tJ84fTFqyW26GqPt9fxy9dW43WMkk1NLCNjN5dKyXfyzLyBW7wxLSr1vMkZfW54YNlh7kTdKCW7RtD6Z70xtxdW3dg3Ym4L55FxN3wJ_9BYZ7M2f9kcRz404 )

At IK, our focus is on helping you become better engineers and through that process help you get your dream jobs. You'll learn everything you need to know to ace any interview, including:

- In-depth understanding of Data Structures and Algorithms, and System Design
- How to handle difficult questions and unseen problems using our unique Power Patterns Methodology
- How to structure your answers for maximum impact
- How to make a positive impression on interviewers

With mock interviews with Mentors and Hiring Managers from FAANG+ companies, you will be able to skip the trial-and-error and get straight to the results you want. Join the webinar to learn how.

If you ghostwrite books for your clients, then you're missing out on a key AI writing trend:

Books are actually AI Training Prompts.

(And even if you don't ghostwrite books, you're going to want to hear about this.)

So, this week I dropped a new video breaking down:

Why books have always been training prompts
The valuable skill non-fiction writers arent monetizing effectively
Why non-fiction writers will write less and less books

And more!

Click here to watch the video over on YouTube.

And if you find it helpful, please let me know in the YouTube comments what your biggest takeaway waswould love to hear it!

Chat soon,

Subject: Your application - Enablement Program Manager, Sales at Datadog
Body Text:
Hi Candace,

Thanks again for your interest in Datadog and the Enablement Program Manager, Sales role. We sincerely appreciate you taking the time to apply with us but this role has been now filled.

We make a point of revisiting past applications on a regular basis to match them to newly opened jobs, so will keep your information handy for future opportunities. Your applicant information will always be stored and processed in accordance with ourApplicant and Candidate Privacy Policy ( https://www.datadoghq.com/legal/applicant-candidate-privacy/ ).

In the meantime, we encourage you to visit our job postings periodically for other roles that might interest you at Datadog via ourCareers page ( https://www.datadoghq.com/careers/ ). You can also learn more about #datadoglife from our employees onLinkedIn ( https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/datadoglife/ ) andInstagram ( https://www.instagram.com/datadoghq/ ).

We wish you the best of luck with your job search!

Kind regards,

The Datadog Recruiting Team

PS: If you've applied to multiple roles at Datadog, you may hear from us more than once.

Subject: FREE video lessons start Monday
Body Text:
Hey Candace,



To celebrate International Coaching Week



Next Monday to Sunday, Im going to be sending you a video lesson each day from inside my Certification School.



Each one of these lessons will give you powerful insights into coaching



and offer you a way to start your path towards becoming a certified life coach.



But, to be fair to my students, I cant leave these unlocked all the time.



So each lesson will only be available for 24 hours.



Starting 7:30am EDT Monday with the first lesson.



Then a new one will appear on Tuesday at 7:30am.



And so on.



So make sure you set a reminder for 7:30am each day to watch the next lesson.



See you then,

Subject: Price increasing - enroll now
Body Text:
Quick note Candace:



On May 1st, the cost to join the Jay Shetty Certification School is going up.



So if youve been thinking about becoming a Jay Shetty certified coach in 2025



This is your moment.



Enroll now and secure your seat before the price increase. ( https://call.jayshettycoaching.com/?el=booking-email-increase-163-5&utm_campaign=booking-be&utm_campaign_name=JSCS%3A+Prospects+Week+163-5&utm_content_name=Price+increasing+-+enroll+now&utm_medium_name=email_action&utm_source_name=customer.io )



But



This moment is NOT just a chance to save - its your chance to step up when the world needs coaches most.



Because right now uncertainty is higher than weve seen in decades



And uncertain times are when coaches really thrive. 

* Jobs and industries are being transformed by new technology
* Future plans are being re-evaluated as the economy shifts
* People are overwhelmed by all the change, trying to find solid ground again


And they desperately need coaches to help them adapt and move forward.



 So they can still create the life theyve worked so hard for

 Still pursue the future they imagined for their family

 And start feeling more normal, more confident, and more certain again

So, joining my coaching Certification School isnt just a smart financial decision



Its your chance to make a real, meaningful impact.



At a time when people are crying out for someone like you to help them.



The first step is right in front of you:



Click here to apply to join my coaching certification school now - before the price increase. ( https://call.jayshettycoaching.com/?el=booking-email-increase-163-5&utm_campaign=booking-be&utm_campaign_name=JSCS%3A+Prospects+Week+163-5&utm_content_name=Price+increasing+-+enroll+now&utm_medium_name=email_action&utm_source_name=customer.io )

Subject: Future-proof new career
Body Text:
Hey Candace,



As Viraj explained in his video I sent you yesterday (check your inbox if you missed it).



No matter how much technology evolves



People are always going to crave human connection.



And look to other humans for guidance.



Its hardwired into our brain as social animals 



In fact



As technology becomes a greater part of our lives, we want even more of that human connection and value it even more.



Despite the fact we can use AI to generate music in minutes and chat to robots 24/7



Demand for in-person events, concerts and experiences is expected to DOUBLE in the next 10 years.



No matter how cool technology is



What we REALLY crave is to connect with a genuine human being who really understands how youre feeling.



Thats just one of the many reasons coaching is such a great, future-proof career. ( https://pages.jayshettycoaching.com/rewarding-career-video-bau-e/?el=RNC-email-future-proof-162-4&utm_campaign_name=JSCS%3A+Prospects+Week+162-4&utm_content_name=Future-proof+new+career&utm_medium_name=email_action&utm_source_name=customer.io )



 Because its built on something timeless: real human connection.



 The kind that makes people feel seen, heard, and supported - by someone who truly understands.

If you want to start a rewarding, new career as a coach in 2025



And learn the future-proof skills you need to connect with others and offer real, meaningful guidance



Then watch this video now - and I'll show you how to get started as a coach ( https://pages.jayshettycoaching.com/rewarding-career-video-bau-e/?el=RNC-email-future-proof-162-4&utm_campaign_name=JSCS%3A+Prospects+Week+162-4&utm_content_name=Future-proof+new+career&utm_medium_name=email_action&utm_source_name=customer.io ).

world-class instructors to bring you the latest creative AI techniques. If
you've ever wanted to have a creative career where you use the latest AI tools,
this pack was designed for you.With the 5 course bundle
[https://uqj77c.ff12.fdske.com/e/c/01jsfj16hb84mq4mv2kkdq879e/01jsfj16hb84mq4mv2kvpzh1tb]

periods. It's 100% on your own schedule.This bundle offer is for all courses at
Curious Refuge:AI Animation

course content all the time to keep you in the know. We got you!Image item

Subject: What You Should Be Tracking Instead of Views
Body Text:
Hey Candace,

Hope youve had a good start to the week 

Weve now finished all our quarterly planning so Ive been back
on the filming train this week - already managed to get two
videos out and it finally feels like Im starting to get some
momentum with it which is a relief 

As Ive said before, we havent uploaded as many videos as we
planned so far this year, and none of the videos have gone viral.
In fact, over the past month weve had quite a few videos perform
quite badly in the first 24hrs - 9 or 10 out of 10 in YouTube
Studio.

One of my team members recently asked if seeing a 10/10 video
in our YouTube Studio made me feel any particular way about the
channel. And to be honest, it never feels great. Despite all the
things I can tell myself about the issues with that out of 10
ranking, its still never great to see a 9 or 10 and I still get
the same feeling of elation when I see the fireworks with a 1 out
of 10.

But I always have to remind myself that views arent everything.

When you only obsess over creating viral hits, not only does it
suck the fun out of being a YouTuber, but youre also chasing the
wrong metric. Instead, you want to find your North Star 

Let me explain

Ive now got over 6 million subscribers, but not every video gets
6 million views. Some of those subscribers are completely
inactivetheyre still subscribed, but theyre not actually
watching anymore. Others, however, are true fans. Not only do
they watch most of my videos, but they also subscribe to my email
newsletters, follow me over on TikTok and Instagram, and take my
courses. Theyre genuinely interested in my content. 

So, the real focus of your YouTube channel needs to be delivering
consistent value to these loyal fans. Forget the obsession with
getting huge view counts on every single video, because when you
focus on this, youll miss the bigger picture. Instead, you want
better engagement and retention from the right people.

And thats why you need a North Star metricto measure how many
true fans you actually have, and whether or not that number is
growing over time. 

Now this isnt an exact science, and Ive always found it pretty
difficult to find the perfect proxy that feels somewhat legit.
But one metric I do find useful is monthly returning viewers -
this is what mine currently looks like:


Just like a software company tracks weekly active users, this
metric gives me a solid sense of how many viewers are coming back
for moreand coming back consistently. For me, monthly also feels
like the right cadence.

But thats not the full story. The balance between creating
content for existing loyal fans and attracting new audiences is
something every creator struggles withmyself included. 

For example, I know that my true fans are way more likely to
watch a vlog where I document my life and they get to see
everything Im up to these days. But vlogs are pretty much
guaranteed to get fewer views than my usual sit down and talk to
the camera content, because most people dont even know who I
am.

On the other hand, a new viewer is more likely to click on a
video titled something like, 9 Passive Incomes Ideas or How I
Manage My Time - The Trident Calendar System - both of which
attracted large numbers of new viewers to the channel which is
obviously needed if you want to continue to grow consistently
too.

Despite always feeling the pain of 9/10 out of 10s, Im
relatively chill about the fact that not every video will be a
banger. Some will go viral, some will totally flop, most will be
somewhere in the middleand thats fine. The key, as Ive always
said, is trying to remain consistent.

Building a content strategy that helps grow your audience without
burning out or chasing trends is exactly the type of stuff we
talk about in PTYA (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/p9ugxvrl5nb9h252p3qsqhpnkk733hr/08hwhgu297d2grsp/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYWxpYWJkYWFsLmNvbS9wYXJ0LXRpbWUteW91dHViZXItYWNhZGVteS8_dXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW5vcnRoc3Rhcl9hcHIxNiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9Y3JlYXRvcm5vdGVz
). So if todays email resonated with you at all, its definitely
worth checking out - heres the link (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/p9ugxvrl5nb9h252p3qsqhpnkk733hr/08hwhgu297d2grsp/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYWxpYWJkYWFsLmNvbS9wYXJ0LXRpbWUteW91dHViZXItYWNhZGVteS8_dXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW5vcnRoc3Rhcl9hcHIxNiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9Y3JlYXRvcm5vdGVz
) 

(And remember, if you join youll also get access to the PTYA
Community which is thriving at the moment and weve got some
exciting guests coming up in May too )

Alternatively, if youre a complete beginner and youre worried
about taking that first step, then you might want to check out
The 7 Video Challenge (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/p9ugxvrl5nb9h252p3qsqhpnkk733hr/vqh3hmuovkpoe9hw/aHR0cHM6Ly9hbGlhYmRhYWwuY29tLzctdmlkZW8tY2hhbGxlbmdlLz91dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bm9ydGhzdGFyX2FwcjE2JnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1jcmVhdG9ybm5vdGVz
) instead. This is something we launched back in January to help
people hit publish on that first video - its a challenge
designed not only to teach you how to create great videos but
also reward you for taking action and connects you with a
supportive community of fellow beginners - check it out here (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/p9ugxvrl5nb9h252p3qsqhpnkk733hr/vqh3hmuovkpoe9hw/aHR0cHM6Ly9hbGlhYmRhYWwuY29tLzctdmlkZW8tY2hhbGxlbmdlLz91dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bm9ydGhzdGFyX2FwcjE2JnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1jcmVhdG9ybm5vdGVz
).

And if you want to keep getting CreatorNotes each week with my
musings and advice on YouTube, thats totally fine too, I love
having this outlet to talk about creator-based stuff 

Have a great week and speak to you next Wednesday 

Ali xx

Body Text:
From: "The Google Workspace Team" [workspace-noreply@google.com]Subject:  Please verify the contact information forprecisiondatainsights.com to avoid service interruption

Reminder to complete setup

## Verify contact information to prevent domain suspension

Hello,

It looks like you haven't verified contact information for your domainprecisiondatainsights.com. Please find your domain registrar verificationemail(https://support.squarespace.com/hc/en-us/articles/205812218-Verifying-your-Squarespace-managed-domain)from Squarespace and follow their instructions to avoid domain suspension.The confirmation message was sent to the email address you used to sign upfor Google Workspace.

If you don't confirm your contact information within 15 days of purchase,Squarespace is required to suspend your domain and you won't be able toreceive emails.

### Your Domain Registration account

**User name:**

admin@precisiondatainsights.com

**Domain:**

precisiondatainsights.com

You're the administrator. To manage all your Domain Registration services,billing, and users sign in to the Admin Console (https://admin.google.com).

Your new domain is registered with Squarespace Domains. For advanced domainsettings

sign in to the Squarespace Domains

using your admin@precisiondatainsights.com account.

### **Need help?**

24/7 support is included with your Domain Registration subscription.

**For Google Workspace:**** **Contact the Google Workspace support team(https://support.google.com/a/answer/1047213?utm_source=9065927&utm_medium=email)or visit the Google Workspace Administrator Help Center(https://support.google.com/a?utm_source=9065927&utm_medium=email).

**For Cloud Identity Premium:**** **Contact the Cloud Identity support team(https://support.google.com/cloudidentity/answer/7664425/?utm_source=9065927&utm_medium=email)or visit the Cloud Identity Help Center(https://support.google.com/cloudidentity?utm_source=9065927&utm_medium=email).Also, set up email with your domain(https://support.google.com/cloudidentity/answer/7667994?utm_source=9065927&utm_medium=email)to create custom email addresses at precisiondatainsights.com.

**For Squarespace Domains: **Visit the Squarespace Domains Help Center(https://support.squarespace.com/hc/en-us/categories/200290497).** **

Sincerely,

The Google Workspace Team

Subject: 4 Strategies To Elevate Your Communication Style From Engineer To Leader
Body Text:
View this post on the web at https://seattledataguy.substack.com/p/4-strategies-to-elevate-your-communication

Hi, fellow future and current Data Leaders; Ben here 
Today, were going to discuss how you can improve communication with the business to gain buy-in for a project or deliver better results and insights.
Before doing that, I wanted to let you know that in July, Ill be hosting several webinars and discussions with data leaders about problems that extend beyond just technology (although well likely touch on some infrastructure topics). So, if youre interested in growing as a data leader, you can sign up here [ https://substack.com/redirect/68d469bf-5db8-49d7-974d-b66cf758885c?j=eyJ1IjoiNTFkc2s3In0.TG_s5GaRal_EYLFDF-UYKHL5eEiDcX8TdL6-5nynlYA ].
Now, lets jump into the article!
One of the challenges many of us technophiles face is well, being technophiles. We love the tools, the architecture, the solutions. We obsess over systems, stacks, and edge cases.
Thats all fineuntil we try to talk to our business stakeholders as if theyre just as obsessed.
We start throwing around abbreviations and technical terms that take years of experience to fully understand.
We slip into jargon. Acronyms. Architecture diagrams. We might be speaking the same language but it goes right over our stakeholders heads.
Inside the data team, that language makes perfect sense. But when we step outside that bubble and talk to non-technical peers the same way, we lose them. Worse, we frustrate them.
So lets talk about how to communicate with the businesswithout technobabbling.
Technobabbling
I dont recall the first time I saw the Rockwell Retro Encabulator video, but it stuck with me. It perfectly illustrates how easy it is to throw around words that are technical but mean absolutely nothing to most people.
If you watched the clip, you probably caught the part where they rattle off a bunch of companies and brands. Its oddly familiarjust like when we say we use Databricks [ https://substack.com/redirect/cd3ea56f-2d94-495f-aa71-8945804b6942?j=eyJ1IjoiNTFkc2s3In0.TG_s5GaRal_EYLFDF-UYKHL5eEiDcX8TdL6-5nynlYA ], Iceberg [ https://substack.com/redirect/dc06bdd5-df94-46fe-b3b4-838d1e6cf4b4?j=eyJ1IjoiNTFkc2s3In0.TG_s5GaRal_EYLFDF-UYKHL5eEiDcX8TdL6-5nynlYA ], Data Lakehouses, Snowflake [ https://substack.com/redirect/0aa715cc-647f-4653-8f32-e20a4c3ad8bc?j=eyJ1IjoiNTFkc2s3In0.TG_s5GaRal_EYLFDF-UYKHL5eEiDcX8TdL6-5nynlYA ], ETLs [ https://substack.com/redirect/41c6ac15-0136-4d42-8b13-fc9be495d0f5?j=eyJ1IjoiNTFkc2s3In0.TG_s5GaRal_EYLFDF-UYKHL5eEiDcX8TdL6-5nynlYA ], or whatevers trending this week.
As if that means anything.
Then you layer in buzzwords and b*llshit, and suddenly, no ones on the same page. Thats exactly how we sound when we point to our architecture diagrams and speak in industry terms.
So, how can you avoid falling into this trap?
SeattleDataGuys Newsletter is a reader-supported publication. To receive new posts and support my work, consider becoming a free or paid subscriber.
1) Frame Everything in Terms of Impact, Not Tools
Once you move past the jargon, theres another common trap: focusing too much on what you built and not enough on why it matters.
You might be proud you used Airflow [ https://substack.com/redirect/b463c1e8-7707-4755-8606-f3544dd187f1?j=eyJ1IjoiNTFkc2s3In0.TG_s5GaRal_EYLFDF-UYKHL5eEiDcX8TdL6-5nynlYA ], Snowflake, or dbt. Maybe you solved a gnarly data issue or implemented a cool new feature. But unless youre talking to a fellow engineer, your stakeholders dont care about your tooling, unless it clearly connects to a business result.
(Ok, sometimes youll get lucky and speak with someone who does geek out over tech. But most of the time? Youre talking to people who care about outcomes.)
This is where impact framing comes in.
As a technical professional, its easy to assume your value lies in solving complex technical problems. But the technical problem is generally a means to an end. Youre being hired for the outcomes your stack makes possible.
So shift your focus. Speak in terms of:
Time saved
Revenue 
Risk reduced
Efficiency gained 
Clarity delivered
Youre still describing the same work. But your framing should change depending on whos in the room. Thats how you make your work resonate beyond the data team [ https://substack.com/redirect/e174706f-a358-443f-87de-8bf18ee7c14c?j=eyJ1IjoiNTFkc2s3In0.TG_s5GaRal_EYLFDF-UYKHL5eEiDcX8TdL6-5nynlYA ].
Tips for Strong Impact Framing
Lead with outcomes, then explain the work - Example: We reduced customer churn alerts from hours to minutes by refactoring the pipeline that feeds the alerting system.
Quantify when you can - Even a rough estimate is better than none. If you saved time, reduced costs, or sped things upsay so.
Name the team or person it helped - Gave the finance team a real-time view of transactions is far more effective than Built a transactions table.
Map it to a business goal - Tie your work back to company-wide initiatives or OKRs. It shows you understand the bigger picture.
For example:
 Without Impact: We implemented automated anomaly detection on key metrics. 
 With Impact: We can now catch revenue-impacting issues like billing spikes within minutes instead of waiting for someone to notice them the next day or week when they manually create their reports.
You can also layer in business context to drive the point home:
 No context: We reduced query costs by $20,000.
 Context: Thats the equivalent of hiring a new analyst for a quarterjust from optimizing five of our most expensive queries.
This kind of framing helps the business understand the weight of what youve delivered. Even better? It gives them an easy win to share up the chain.
2) Highlight the Cost of Inaction
Sometimes, the best way to persuade the business isnt by pitching the benefits, its by making the risks of doing nothing crystal clear.
As a consultant, Ill often ask prospects a simple question:
"What if you didnt hire me? or Why not just invest the money elsewhere?
Its a great way to reframe the conversation and surface the urgency.
A common case of inaction? When business executives want to fast-track ahead, skipping foundational data engineering work [ https://substack.com/redirect/8b51dcb4-637f-4ff4-b582-12b17fe38388?j=eyJ1IjoiNTFkc2s3In0.TG_s5GaRal_EYLFDF-UYKHL5eEiDcX8TdL6-5nynlYA ]. It feels like progress in the short term, but it introduces hidden risks that dont show up until its too late.
The key is to make those risks tangible. Use clear business language, potential financial impacts, or missed opportunities.
How to Surface the Risk
To effectively communicate the cost of inaction:
Point to a past failure (yours or one from another company)
Estimate the financial or operational impact of things going wrong
Use if this, then that framing to make the risk tangible
This kind of framing works especially well when the stakeholders are underestimating the importance of a technical investment, or pushing to move fast by skipping steps. It happens often, especially in tech environments where speed is prized over process.
3) Use Maturity Models to Set Realistic Expectations
Right now, just about every data team, whether its a solo analyst or a 100,000-person org, is being asked to deliver AI and ML. But the question is: Are they ready?
Do you need the perfect BI infrastructure in place to run AI? Not necessarily. But if youre still struggling to do BI well, trying to layer AI on top is a red flag.
Thats where maturity models come in.
A maturity model gives you a shared language for showing where the company is right now and what needs to happen before more advanced capabilities can be successful. It helps you frame the conversation around progress instead of resistance.
Instead of saying, Were not ready for that, you can say:
Were still in the crawl stage. Jumping to AI before we can reliably report on the basics is like trying to fly before weve learned to walk.
This allows you to provide a path forward instead of an all out no.
It also builds trust. Youre not just pointing out limitations, youre showing leadership by mapping the next step forward.
How to Use Maturity Models Effectively
Use visuals. Draw the ladder, phase chart, or journey map on a slide or whiteboard to make the concept more tangible.
Plot your current state. Show where the company sits today and where it wants to go.
Frame it as progress, not limitation. Emphasize that growth is possible with the right investments.
4) Use Analogies That Make Sense to Your Audience
One of the most powerful tools in your communication toolkit is the analogy, especially when it connects to something your stakeholder already understands.
Talking to someone in manufacturing? Explain data pipelines like assembly lines: data comes in as raw materials, gets cleaned and shaped, and turns into something useful on the other end.
Talking to someone in finance? Frame data quality issues like bad inputs in a financial model, garbage in, garbage out.
The best analogies are:
Relevant to the stakeholders domain
Simple enough to land without extra explanation
The key is meeting people where they are, not expecting them to come to you.
Final Thoughts
Its tempting to talk to the business the same way you talk to your data team. But the business has different goals, different priorities, and a completely different frame of reference.
Thats why its important to first understand your audiencewho you are delivering to, then shape your message accordingly.
Use analogies. Speak in terms of impact. Frame the work in ways that make sense to them. Thats how you get buy-in. Thats how you build trust.
Not by confusing stakeholders with technobabble.
As always, thanks for reading.
Join My Data Engineering And Data Science Discord
If youre looking to talk more about data engineering, data science, breaking into your first job, and finding other like minded data specialists. Then you should join the Seattle Data Guy discord!
We are now over 8000 members!
Join My Technical Consultants Community
If youre a data consultant or considering becoming one then you should join the Technical Freelancer Community! We have over 1700 members!
Youll find plenty of free resources you can access to expedite your journey as a technical consultant as well as be able to talk to other consultants about questions you may have!
Articles Worth Reading
There are thousands of new articles posted daily all over the web! I have spent a lot of time sifting through some of these articles as well as TechCrunch and companies tech blog and wanted to share some of my favorites!
7 Unwritten Rules for High-Impact Engineering Careers
When I joined the semiconductor industry 15 years ago, I was about as bright-eyed and bushy tailed as a fresh college graduate can be  excited to be a force to reckon with, eager to make a positive contribution, and ready for a steady climb up the career ladder.
As the years rolled by, I learned that things are a lot more complicated than that. For example, companies are not all that meritocratic as they claim to be. Or that proving youre right today has consequences in the long term because people have feelings. And hold grudges. Most notably, it is often about who you know than what you do.
Time is the best teacher of the unwritten dynamics of chip design companies.
Read More Here [ https://substack.com/redirect/843dd349-0e3a-4801-8adf-392adf3d95b1?j=eyJ1IjoiNTFkc2s3In0.TG_s5GaRal_EYLFDF-UYKHL5eEiDcX8TdL6-5nynlYA ]
The Basics of SFTP: Authentication, Encryption, and File Management
If youre looking to pass hundreds of GBs of data quickly, youre likely not going to use a REST API.
Thats why every day, companies share data sets of users, patient claims, financial transactions, and more via SFTP.
If youve been in the industry for a while, youve probably come across automated SFTP jobs that do just that. Youve also likely had to encrypt or decrypt a CSV and had to interpret a schema file with parsing instructions thatsomehoware always a bit off the first time.
Now, sure, we all want to build real-time systems that use LLMs and other flashy new tools and solutions. Sometimes, thats not what is called for.
After all, companies of all sizeseven tech giants like Facebook and Airbnbstill use SFTP to share critical information for analytical purposes(as well as operational). So, lets dig into what SFTP is and how you will likely work with it.
Read More Here [ https://substack.com/redirect/e1dc23a8-710b-4030-89c1-8b45ecfd2583?j=eyJ1IjoiNTFkc2s3In0.TG_s5GaRal_EYLFDF-UYKHL5eEiDcX8TdL6-5nynlYA ]

If you decide to enable two-factor authentication, ensure you retain access to one or more account recovery methods. See https://docs.github.com/articles/configuring-two-factor-authentication-recovery-methods in the GitHub Help.

Thanks,
The GitHub Team

Subject: Thank you for your application to LifeSOULutions That Work!
Body Text:
This is preheader text. Some clients will show this text as a preview. Hello
Brave Thinker!

Academics West shared a post: May is Mental Health Awareness Month and were highlighting an unexpected (and furry!) form of support: therapy dogs. 

Did you know that petting a dog can release stress-reducing hormones and boost emotional well-being? At Academics West, canine therapy is more than a feel-good moment. Its part of our integrated therapeutic model that supports students where they are, emotionally and academically.

In a new blog post, our Co-founder Dr. Evan Flamenbaum, MA, DSW dives into the science behind animal-assisted in-house interventions and how our in-house therapy dog KOA helps students regulate, reconnect, and thrive.

Tap into the power of paws! Read the article below: https://lnkd.in/gD_Y6veN

Subject: Why You Should Set Your Vision Before 2026
Body Text:
Hey friends,

Quick thing before we start - weve recently made some updates
and changes to Momentum (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/o8u2p8v079tqh6g8klxuvhq4dm8rrcohqe49l/6qhehoullozpq7c9/aHR0cHM6Ly9nby5zcGFya2xlLnNvL21vbWVudHVtL3Byb2Rub3Rlc18xMw==
), the app that we launched last month, so if youve not tried it
yet, you can download it and get a 3-day free trial here (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/o8u2p8v079tqh6g8klxuvhq4dm8rrcohqe49l/6qhehoullozpq7c9/aHR0cHM6Ly9nby5zcGFya2xlLnNvL21vbWVudHVtL3Byb2Rub3Rlc18xMw==
). (Were aiming to launch the Android version within the next
couple of weeks - please bear with us, it is coming!)

Hope you had a great weekend 

Were now back into the swing of a normal working routine after a
couple of disrupted weeks with the team offsite followed by a
week of food poisoning which wasn't great but did give me more
time to consume more Harry Potter fan fiction 

Anyway, I wanted to use todays email to reflect on the vision
board I made back in January when my wife Izzy hosted a vision
boarding workshop as part of our annual planning event. And yes,
well be running another one of these in 2026 - Ill announce it
in these emails when weve got dates sorted 

A vision board is essentially this powerful pictorial
representation of your goals, dreams, and aspirations, and this
is what mine looked like at the start of the year:


Izzy and I had our first kid. We literally just moved into our
new team office here in Hong Kong the other week. Weve launched
another app called Momentum (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/o8u2p8v079tqh6g8klxuvhq4dm8rrcohqe49l/6qhehoullozpq7c9/aHR0cHM6Ly9nby5zcGFya2xlLnNvL21vbWVudHVtL3Byb2Rub3Rlc18xMw==
). And while Im not doing martial arts anymore, Ive gotten
really into tennis instead, which I personally find way more fun
and energising.

Now Im not saying Ive ticked everything off - obviously I
havent. But looking back at this vision board I threw together
in 15 minutes at the start of the year, Im genuinely surprised
by how much has shifted in the right direction.

I always remind my LifeOS (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/o8u2p8v079tqh6g8klxuvhq4dm8rrcohqe49l/58hvh8ugg7q5ekf7/aHR0cHM6Ly9hbGlhYmRhYWwuY29tL2xpZmVvcy8_dXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPXZpc2lvbl8xMyZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9cHJvZG5vdGVz
) students that its really difficult to make any kind of
meaningful change in your life if you dont have a compelling
vision for where you want to go.

You dont need to know exactly where you want to end up - life
has a habit of punching us in the face sometimes anyway  But you
do need some sort of direction to aim towards, because if your
ideal vision for the future doesnt actually feel better or more
exciting than where you are right now, then theres no motivation
to make changes happen.

And thats exactly what a vision board does - it gives you that
direction.

By looking at your vision board daily, youre also signalling to
a part of your brain called the Reticular Activating System (RAS)
that these goals are important to you.

Your RAS acts like a filter for all the sensory information
youre constantly bombarded with - everything from what you see
and hear to random thoughts - and it categorises about 99% of it
as not important, letting it pass by unnoticed.

But when you regularly look at your vision board, youre flagging
those images and goals as important, which means your RAS
suddenly starts noticing opportunities related to them that you
might have missed before.

Just to be clear: a vision board isnt a magical manifestation
tool. And by sticking a bunch of pictures on a board, Im not
saying the universe will deliver your dream on a silver platter.

Instead, a vision board is a focus tool.

I still had to actually search for office spaces (or delegate
this to Becky on the team ), build the apps, and show up to
tennis practice but the vision board just helped me clarify my
goals and keep them front of mind.

This whole concept of visualising your life a few years from now
is part of The Future Sketch module in LifeOS (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/o8u2p8v079tqh6g8klxuvhq4dm8rrcohqe49l/58hvh8ugg7q5ekf7/aHR0cHM6Ly9hbGlhYmRhYWwuY29tL2xpZmVvcy8_dXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPXZpc2lvbl8xMyZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9cHJvZG5vdGVz
), where we explore different methods for creating a compelling
vision thats actually aligned with your values - check it out
here (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/o8u2p8v079tqh6g8klxuvhq4dm8rrcohqe49l/58hvh8ugg7q5ekf7/aHR0cHM6Ly9hbGlhYmRhYWwuY29tL2xpZmVvcy8_dXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPXZpc2lvbl8xMyZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9cHJvZG5vdGVz
) if youre interested.

But even if you don't join LifeOS (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/o8u2p8v079tqh6g8klxuvhq4dm8rrcohqe49l/58hvh8ugg7q5ekf7/aHR0cHM6Ly9hbGlhYmRhYWwuY29tL2xpZmVvcy8_dXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPXZpc2lvbl8xMyZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9cHJvZG5vdGVz
), Id genuinely encourage you to spend 15 minutes this week
throwing together a quick vision board.

It doesnt need to be fancy or perfect. Just grab a few images
that make you think yeah, that would be cool and stick them
somewhere youll see regularly (whether thats digitally or
physically).

Let me know how you get on - hit reply and feel free to share it
with me.

Have a great week!

Ali xx

Subject: Welcome to Designlab!
Body Text:
Welcome to Designlab!

We're so excited that you're a part of our vibrant (and still growing!) design network.

You'll receive a copy of The Brief, a curated compilation of the best UX/UI design articles in your inbox each week.

We've helped thousands of professionals from all backgrounds successfully shift and grow their careers in the field of UX/UI design, and we hope to do the same for you.

We're here to support you however we canwhether that's sharing the latest design trends and resources, or making ourselves available to chat 1:1 about your career ambitions.

Launch your career in UX/UI design

Subject: The Key to Sustainable Productivity
Body Text:
Hey Candace,

Hope you had a great weekend and enjoyed the Spring Reset
workshop on Saturday if you were able to make it.

Just as a reminder, if you werent able to attend, you can access
the recording here (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/lmur20nw6mimhn4e0n6s6h8r5e000cg/kkhmh2undr77kdhk/aHR0cHM6Ly9hbGlhYmRhYWwuY29tL2NvbmZpcm1hdGlvbi9zcHJpbmctcmVzZXQtd29ya3Nob3AtcmV3YXRjaC1jb25maXJtYXRpb24v
) and all the links, resources and tools will be linked on that
page too.

As I mentioned last Monday, the purpose of these quarterly
reviews is really to focus on the piece of the productivity
puzzle thats often missing from traditional advice - your
vision.

In other words, making sure that youre actually heading in the
right direction and your actions are genuinely aligned with your
goals.

Productivity isnt really about just getting more done - ticking
off to-dos or powering through tasks - because theres no point
in doing that if youre heading in the wrong direction and your
actions arent aligned with your vision.

Thats a recipe for burnout not sustainable productivity.

And thats why I created LifeOS (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/lmur20nw6mimhn4e0n6s6h8r5e000cg/58hvh8ugvqeernf7/aHR0cHM6Ly9hbGlhYmRhYWwuY29tL2xpZmVvcy8_dXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmRheV8zMSZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9cG9zdF9ldmVudF9zZXF1ZW5jZQ==
).

LifeOS (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/lmur20nw6mimhn4e0n6s6h8r5e000cg/58hvh8ugvqeernf7/aHR0cHM6Ly9hbGlhYmRhYWwuY29tL2xpZmVvcy8_dXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmRheV8zMSZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9cG9zdF9ldmVudF9zZXF1ZW5jZQ==
) isnt just another productivity course or collection of random
tipsits a complete operating system for your life and work,
built around a philosophy that transforms how you approach
productivity based on two key pillars - vision and action.

In fact, its the integration of these two pillars which is what
makes LifeOS (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/lmur20nw6mimhn4e0n6s6h8r5e000cg/58hvh8ugvqeernf7/aHR0cHM6Ly9hbGlhYmRhYWwuY29tL2xpZmVvcy8_dXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmRheV8zMSZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9cG9zdF9ldmVudF9zZXF1ZW5jZQ==
) particularly powerful because when you combine clarity of
vision with a system built for effective action you:

* Procrastinate less because you understand the why behind each
task
* Experience less decision fatigue as your values and goals guide
your choices
* Maintain more consistent motivation by connecting daily actions
to meaningful outcomes.

LifeOS isnt about working harderits about aligning your
efforts with what truly matters and creating systems that make
progress automatic.

Plus if you join this week, youll also get access to the 2025
April Sprint - an exclusive 3 week event that were running for
our LifeOS Pro members but that were offering as a bonus to
anyone who signs up to LifeOS before 2259 GMT on Friday 4th April
(this Friday ).

--> Click Here to Join Today (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/lmur20nw6mimhn4e0n6s6h8r5e000cg/58hvh8ugvqeernf7/aHR0cHM6Ly9hbGlhYmRhYWwuY29tL2xpZmVvcy8_dXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmRheV8zMSZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9cG9zdF9ldmVudF9zZXF1ZW5jZQ==
)
 Click Here to Join Today (
https://aliabdaal.com/lifeos/?utm_source=post_event_sequence&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=monday_31
)If youve got any questions, queries or concerns, just hit reply
or email support@aliabdaal.com.

Tomorrow Ill talk about the missing piece of the puzzle and why
I didnt just want to create a course - there was something more

Stay tuned 

Ali x

P.S - If you joined the call on Saturday, youll know we had a
couple of slight issues with the Voicepal (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/lmur20nw6mimhn4e0n6s6h8r5e000cg/25h2h9u3v655kgh8/aHR0cHM6Ly9nby5hbGlhYmRhYWwuY29tL3ZvaWNlcGFsL3Bvc3Rfc3ByaW5ncmVzZXQ=
) demo and, as an apology, were extending the free trial an
additional 7 days (until April 7th) so youve got another week to
use the journalling and brainstorming frameworks that we launched
as part of that demo. Download the app here (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/lmur20nw6mimhn4e0n6s6h8r5e000cg/25h2h9u3v655kgh8/aHR0cHM6Ly9nby5hbGlhYmRhYWwuY29tL3ZvaWNlcGFsL3Bvc3Rfc3ByaW5ncmVzZXQ=

[https://www.oracle.com/a/ocom/img/orc-header.jpg] 
Hi  Candace, 

Here's a reminder about your draft job application
[https://careers.oracle.com/jobs/#s/Fzu3T1Z94p]for Principal Program Manager
that has not been completed by you. We'd love to learn more about your interest
in this position while it remains open, so make sure to complete all required
steps if you'd like to be considered. 

If you don't complete your job application, the data you entered will be stored
for 30 days and then deleted. After that, you will need to start the job
application process over again. If you decide you're no longer interested in
this opportunity or other opportunities at Oracle, you can delete the data
[https://careers.oracle.com/jobs/#s/cEBqadkmlk]you entered. 

Thanks for your interest in a career at Oracle! 

Kind regards,
Oracle Talent Acquisition

Subject: Explore Wikimedia's Knowledge with Kaggle!
Body Text:
Kaggle







Hi Candace Grant,

We're excited to announce a new collaboration between Kaggle and theWikimedia Foundation, the nonprofit behind Wikipedia.

As part of Wikimedia's mission to make all knowledge freely accessible anduseful, Wikimedia is publishing a beta version of its structured content onKaggle in French and English. This release gives data scientists,researchers, and machine learning enthusiasts a new, streamlined way toexplore and analyze this global information resource. In the spirit ofdemocratizing data, you're invited to not only explore the information, butto participate in improving and updating it. We're very excited to hearwhat you discover!





Learn More



You can now:


 Discover the new Wikimedia datasets
 Analyze them in Kaggle Notebooks
 Join the conversation in our forums
 Download and reuse the data in your own projects
 Read Wikimedia Enterprise's announcement


Let's turn open knowledge into deeper insights.

Happy Kaggling!

Brenda Flynn
Kaggle Partnerships Lead



Kaggle, Inc 1600 Amphitheatre Pkwy Mountain View, CA 94043

This email was sent to aicoaching2025@gmail.com because you indicated thatyou'd like to receive news and updates about Kaggle. If you don't want toreceive these emails in the future, please unsubscribe here. You can alsochange your preferences on your account's profile page by logging in atkaggle.com.

Subject: The Immersion Experience at UC Berkeley
Body Text:
<https://ischoolonline.berkeley.edu/data-science/>

The Immersion Experience at UC Berkeley
 
Dear Prospective Student,
 
As a Master of Information and Data Science (MIDS) student, the immersion is your opportunity to meet faculty and peers in-person on the UC Berkeley campus or in other locations relevant to data science. You will have the opportunity to gain on-the-ground perspectives from faculty and industry leaders, meet with data science professionals, and soak up more of the School of Information (I School) culture.
 
"I was most looking forward to seeing how different companies like Netflix used analytics to drive value and enhance their business proposition. My biggest takeaway was that analytics is very powerful, but can be challenging to implement! By far, spending time with my classmates was the most memorable experience. After taking over a year of classes with many of them, seeing them in person was a wonderful experience. We went out, explored Berkeley, and had a great time!"
- Filip Krunic, datascience@berkeley graduate
 
"The immersion has built a sense of community amongst my classmates in just three days. It was amazing to interact with individuals from so many different backgrounds and experiences. This immersion has left me with friendships that I know will live on past the length of the program."
- Nitin Kohli, datascience@berkeley graduate
 
"Visiting Uber was an amazing experience. After a 40-minute presentation, we spent over an hour asking questions to Kevin Novak (leader of the data science division) on everything from data science at Uber, to data science at small startups, to the evolving place of data science in the world. It was invaluable to get an inside perspective of data science in the tech world  I left inspired, and with a better idea of the kinds of problems I might like to solve next."
- Chris Llop, datascience@berkeley graduate
 
ACCESS YOUR APPLICATION >>
<https://apply.datascience.berkeley.edu/signup>
No GRE/GMAT Required
 
Complete your application <https://apply.datascience.berkeley.edu/signup> to begin earning your Master of Information and Data Science degree this September. The priority application deadline is April 23. Contact your Admissions Counselor directly at 855-678-6437 or slee2@datascience.berkeley.edu with any questions.

Applications received by the priority application deadline may be eligible for an application fee waiver. In order to ensure you're eligible, please notify your Admissions Counselor by phone or in writing at least 48 hours ahead of submitting your application so we can process your fee waiver request. If you do not receive the fee waiver confirmation email and pay an application fee, we will not be able to reimburse you.
 
Sincerely,
 
datascience@berkeley Admissions
UC Berkeley School of Information
ischoolonline.berkeley.edu <https://ischoolonline.berkeley.edu/data-science/>
855-678-6437

<https://www.linkedin.com/company/berkeley-ischool-online/>
<https://www.facebook.com/BerkeleyISchoolOnline/>
<https://twitter.com/BerkeleyData>

855-678-MIDS | <https://ischoolonline.berkeley.edu/data-science/>

Subject: Mid-Career Fellowships | July 6, 2025
Body Text:
Mid-career fellowships, tips, events and more Dear ProFellow readers, Did you know ProFellow was featured as a key resource in Katrina McGhee's bestselling book "Taking A Career Break For Dummies" [https://www.amazon.com/Taking-Career-Dummies-Katrina-McGhee/dp/1394197594?_encoding=UTF8&pd_rd_w=7QAgY&content-id=amzn1.sym.5f7e0a27-49c0-47d3-80b2-fd9271d863ca:amzn1.symc.e5c80209-769f-4ade-a325-2eaec14b8e0e&pf_rd_p=5f7e0a27-49c0-47d3-80b2-fd9271d863ca&pf_rd_r=D5Z6QV9XQHWFX3EXEWAJ&pd_rd_wg=YyNqN&pd_rd_r=5202daa1-e354-4708-bbe4-aa01fdd5ecf5&linkCode=sl1&tag=kmcghee23-20&linkId=50ba126757e5e4f1eff9c8f995fb9d0b&language=en_US&ref_=as_li_ss_tl]? To help readers identify ways to take a sabbatical or pause, she shares in the book: >"Ifyourdesiretotakeabreakiscenteredonlearning,growthand >newexperiences,youcanconsideraprofessionalfellowshiptofund >yourexperience. >Socialimpactorganizationsprovidefellowshipstoprofessionalswho >cansupportandadvancetheirmissionviaproject-basedwork. > > > >Projectscanlastweeksormonthsandtakeplaceallovertheglobe. >Herearefourfellowshipexamplesformid-careerprofessionals >[_note:IaddedtheProFellowdatabaselinks!_] > > >*AsiaGlobalFellowsProgram >[https://profellow.krtra.com/c/Stx0Acnfkb9c/xeLlP] >leadersandexpertscollaborateonglobalissuesrelatedtoAsia >*EisenhowerFellowshipsGlobalProgram >[https://profellow.krtra.com/c/L5kMIGi9zWoQ/xeLlP]- >professionalandpersonaldevelopmentopportunitiesforleadersfrom >adiversemixofsectors >*FulbrightSpecialistProgram >[https://profellow.krtra.com/c/czpoun9mCrrK/xeLlP]- >connectsU.S.professionalswithinternationalhostinstitutionsfor >shortproject-basedexchanges >*PeaceCorpsResponseProgram >[https://profellow.krtra.com/c/anp3gvts4IYf/xeLlP]- >short-term,high-impactprojectstosupporturgentneedsacrossthe >world > > > >Todiscovermoreoptions,youcanaccessacomprehensivefellowship >databaseatPROFELLOW.COM." We are big fans of Katrina McGhee's work and love being featured in books like this! This helps spread the word about our resources for career advancement. Speaking of which, one way you can support ProFellow's work to expand access to opportunities and keep our comprehensive fellowships and graduate school database paywall-free is by joining one of our workshops! In our workshops, you'll learn insider strategies to achieve these unique awards. UPCOMING WORKSHOP - EARLY PRICING ON NOW! [https://profellow.krtra.com/c/jGFLZmqNugZa/xeLlP] MID-CAREER FELLOWSHIPS Mid-Career Professional Development Award (Fulbright Finland) [https://profellow.krtra.com/c/WzUPrAZHIelF/xeLlP]:Supports experienced professionals taking a 45-month sabbatical for education, training, or practical projects, excluding academic research or lecturing. Benefits include a stipend and travel. Deadline: September 15 VIA Global Community Fellowship [https://profellow.krtra.com/c/LQZ15GgdPjdT/xeLlP]:A 15-month program supporting community development and youth education across Asia for graduates and professionals with a bachelor's. Deadline: October 26 CFR International Affairs Fellowship in Japan [https://profellow.krtra.com/c/KoymUkB93vCp/xeLlP]:Offers U.S. mid-career professionals 312 months in Japan to enhance U.S.-Japan relations through research and professional activities. The application will open in September 2025. Keep working hard and I hope to see you in my upcoming workshop! Subject: One Year From Now
Body Text:
Hey Candace,

Hope youre having a good day.

Weve just wrapped up quarterly planning on our team offsite here
in Hong Kong - its always nice to work with the team in-person
like this, we always come away with a greater sense of clarity
for the months ahead.

Weve been doing these quarterly offsites for a couple of years
now - each time reviewing our 3-year vision for the company, our
annual goals and then planning the next 90 days on a more
granular level.

Looking forward like this - imagining what you want that future
state to look like - isnt just important in business, it matters
on a personal level too.

Just fast forward one year to April 2nd 2026.

Were 365 days further forward in your own life.

What do you imagine youve achieved by that point?

Did you follow through on the goals you set at the Spring Reset?

If youre anything like me, it can be difficult to put yourself
in that space - sometimes its hard to predict whats going to
happen next week 

But its important to imagine what the path to that future state
looks like so that you can align your daily, weekly and monthly
actions to make sure youre heading in the right direction.

That was the whole point of doing the future-facing exercises on
Saturday during the Spring Reset to ensure that youre able to
stay aligned and take consistent action towards your goals. (If
you missed it, you can still access the recording here (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/0vu4o3k67va9h9xep2qhlhvleex55hn/6qhehoulkeq942f9/aHR0cHM6Ly9hbGlhYmRhYWwuY29tL2NvbmZpcm1hdGlvbi9zcHJpbmctcmVzZXQtd29ya3Nob3AtcmV3YXRjaC1jb25maXJtYXRpb24v
)).

Similar questions were being asked this time last year by
students signing up to LifeOS Pro - or Productivity Lab as it was
called then - and some of them have seen incredible
transformations over the past 12 months of being part of the
community.

Take Frida who dreamed of building her own business and YouTube
channel, but her demanding corporate role had left her feeling
drained. LifeOS Pro offered her a structured approach to
rebuilding her focus and clarity. Eight months later, Frida had
left her corporate job to build her own company and by applying
the Labs principle of focusing on one thing that moves you
forward, shes making steady progress without burning out.

Or take Zaim whos biggest challenge was finding the
accountability and structured time he needed to truly level up
his side business. That accountability came quickly through
LifeOS Pros daily Focus Labs which enabled him to establish a
rhythm, showing up every morning and even late at night when
needed. This intense commitment led to incredible progress. In
just six weeks, his income from his side hustle doubled, and by
the end of two months, he was consistently bringing in five
figures monthly. Its the accountability. Setting goals each
session and knowing others were with me on the journeyit changed
everything.

Frida and Zaim didnt have some sort of secret code to
productivity, they just leveraged the spaces and accountability
provided by the community to regularly reflect on their vision
and build a system to take consistent daily actions that compound
into those longer-term transformations.

If you want to follow in their footsteps and invest in achieving
your goals, click here (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/0vu4o3k67va9h9xep2qhlhvleex55hn/kkhmh2undv7xp8ik/aHR0cHM6Ly9hbGlhYmRhYWwuY29tL2xpZmVvcy8_dXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPXdlZG5lc2RheV8yJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1wb3N0X2V2ZW50X3NlcXVlbmNl
) to sign up to LifeOS Pro.

And if you feel like you dont need the accountability but you
still want to take your personal productivity more seriously, you
can join LifeOS instead - just click here (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/0vu4o3k67va9h9xep2qhlhvleex55hn/kkhmh2undv7xp8ik/aHR0cHM6Ly9hbGlhYmRhYWwuY29tL2xpZmVvcy8_dXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPXdlZG5lc2RheV8yJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1wb3N0X2V2ZW50X3NlcXVlbmNl
).

And if you think youve got everything in hand when it comes to
productivity, thats totally fine too - I hope you found the
event on Saturday useful and youve set yourself up for success
throughout the remainder of 2025 

Speak soon

Ali x

P.S - If you buy LifeOS (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/0vu4o3k67va9h9xep2qhlhvleex55hn/kkhmh2undv7xp8ik/aHR0cHM6Ly9hbGlhYmRhYWwuY29tL2xpZmVvcy8_dXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPXdlZG5lc2RheV8yJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1wb3N0X2V2ZW50X3NlcXVlbmNl
) before 2259 GMT on April 4th, youll also be able to join our
exclusive 2025 April Sprint which is a 3-week live event run by
our Productivity coaches focussed on the Action pillar of the
LifeOS philosophy.

Subject: The battle for New York
Body Text: The Economist https://click.e.economist.com/?qs=3238886819a4cb5f5d86904538a57325d983f978491170759de35a8f4c21059ee298f3fbaa73f55f4f28853314a93f546d1ec1aa9e20e2c0b2c9446744cdd52f https://view.e.economist.com/?qs=148e8136a979d094ec13c788192266370e934ee97d3f899c5b0e05a60042360e684d0e27132f31992dc99e13e1f7164ca649dedb0aba4b895548a595de934472c00f0c1a252ddb29a7c6513ec2eae00f Read in browser October 30th 2025 The Economist this week Highlights from the latest issue https://click.e.economist.com/?qs=3238886819a4cb5f1622d1111403f6532c6818f72bc7fd187c876444b3953e803326bb03ba394c5bf1706d4e12000cf2e0520916ae2350f2568009cf3df3affa https://click.e.economist.com/?qs=3238886819a4cb5febfe973b914f2f809a38dfd1987d85a386bd6117f1907460e9288d526f1414ba93b78947058eb803ae75ee79bfbc7f3b https://click.e.economist.com/?qs=3238886819a4cb5f3111831af78eb9b6f9b1261887f26f24381affd6e16dbc98eaa6b527fbfe7360786209ca4a253f062d88c77fd9d73dc2 Edward Carr Deputy editor Sometimes I think that coverage of Ukraine has become bogged down—a bit like the war itself. Because the front line is not moving, neither is the story. Away from the battlefield, though, the wheels continue to turn. https://click.e.economist.com/?qs=3238886819a4cb5febfe973b914f2f809a38dfd1987d85a386bd6117f1907460e9288d526f1414ba93b78947058eb803ae75ee79bfbc7f3b Our cover in Europe this week is a good example. Ukraine is facing a savage cash crunch. Unless something changes, it will run out of money at the end of February. To keep it in the fight, indebted Europe needs to find a lot of money. It would be a mistake to see this cash call as merely a painful exercise in annual budgeting. Instead, it is a historic opportunity to shift the balance of power between Europe and Russia by exposing the Kremlin’s financial frailty. The price of supporting Ukraine is higher than most Europeans realise, but it is also a bargain. Elsewhere https://click.e.economist.com/?qs=3238886819a4cb5f3111831af78eb9b6f9b1261887f26f24381affd6e16dbc98eaa6b527fbfe7360786209ca4a253f062d88c77fd9d73dc2 our cover is about New York —one of the world’s great cities, a source of immense financial and political power, and a place that is about to elect a Democratic Socialist as its mayor. Zohran Mamdani is a new kind of politician, inspiring, optimistic and a rebuke to the tired, predictable Democratic party machine. Mr Mamdani has built his campaign around the idea that life in New York has become too expensive. He is right, but his solutions—which include rent control, a higher minimum wage, free bus travel and so on—would be a disaster for the city. Meanwhile, a New Yorker 45 years his senior is itching to “straighten out” the city of his birth. Working from Washington, Donald Trump could use the flow of federal money and an immigration clampdown to whip up trouble. It’s a theme that Zanny Minton Beddoes, our editor-in-chief, and I https://click.e.economist.com/?qs=3238886819a4cb5f95f4d08d40dbb23aab4958aad7a28e4b673cc58c9b50dd8091dbc88bb8467bb7e982898d3da666d75fe086338ead2e97 discussed on The Insider this week, with two of the stars from our Checks and Balance podcast, Charlotte Howard and John Prideaux. We fear a Trump-Mamdani grudge match with New York as its stage and victim. June 2025











Congrats grads!


Its graduation season, a time for thinking about the future. For someone 
starting their career in tech, that could mean pursuing any variety of paths, 
from AI Engineer to UX Designer. Of course, you dont need to have just 
graduated to be open to new possibilities. Now's a great time to enroll in a 
career path, start a new project, or attend an event  read on for inspiration 
as you consider what step you'll take next.




Heres to new beginnings,

The Codecademy Team

Become a UX Designer


UX design isnt just about creating nice-looking apps or websites. For 
businesses, a great user experience means more satisfied customers, and for 
individuals it means usable, accessible products. In our new UX Designer career 
path, youll learn the foundations of UX design including user research, 
wireframing, and interaction design, then apply them through hands-on projects 
using industry-standard tools.

Subject: AIMO 2025 Progress Prize 2 Competition Wrap-Up!
Body Text:
Kaggle







Hi Candace Grant,

The AI Mathematical Olympiad (AIMO) 2025 Progress Prize 2 competition hasofficially concluded!

This year's challenge asked participants to develop algorithms and modelscapable of solving complex math problems. The competition brought togethera diverse and talented community, all working to advance AI's capabilitiesin mathematical reasoning.

We're excited to share that participants tackled an even more challengingdataset this year and delivered outstanding results. The top performingsolution achieved an impressive 68% accuracy rate, a significantimprovement over last year, highlighting the rapid progress being made inthe field of AI-driven mathematical problem-solving.

To dive into the winning approaches and explore key takeaways from thecompetition, check out the leaderboard and winner solution write-ups below:





View the Leaderboard



Happy Kaggling!

The Kaggle Team



Kaggle, Inc 1600 Amphitheatre Pkwy Mountain View, CA 94043

This email was sent to aicoaching2025@gmail.com because you indicated thatyou'd like to receive news and updates about Kaggle. If you don't want toreceive these emails in the future, please unsubscribe here. You can alsochange your preferences on your account's profile page by logging in atkaggle.com.

Subject: Save your spot for Newselas Back-to-School Kickoff events!
Body Text:
TeacherNewsletter
June 26, 2025
Hi friends,

You've earned this summer break, and we want to help you keep it relaxing! Theres no better way to do that than to get a head start on the new school year by saving your spot early for our Back-to-School Kickoff Webinars <https://eml.newsela.com/NjI4LVpQRS01MTAAAAGbS69k_CO4SZBOSzax3LIN7TheoXmEE-87JRyIdhQKxDf4q9aPKfi4tMfUSChWNUE4xci08E0=>.

We're preparing sessions packed with strategies and resources just for you, including our AI Keynote, dedicated 101 sessions if you're new to Newsela or Formative, and a "For Teachers by Teachers" series featuring insights from real educators in real classrooms.

🚀 Lets do this!

See you next month,
Kara
Register Early!
Tuesday, July 29th: Foundations for Success



	- AI in Education: Approaches to Purposeful Adoption <https://eml.newsela.com/NjI4LVpQRS01MTAAAAGbS69k_PVWm-hrihs-WWWlXSjEAoHb491Nf9MsFzBroSFeFEz3hVzpPazqYNhyhNlZzZGewSY=>: Explore AI's potential in education and Newsela's vision for personalized learning and teacher support.
	- Newsela 101: Building Routines <https://eml.newsela.com/NjI4LVpQRS01MTAAAAGbS69k_PCBEUHTlIhbDqP6FqBvqXarWClyLebBusW3qIQJq1bLL2FUAAVZd1nk_j76xd8TSok=>: New to Newsela? Start strong with ready-to-use resources and strategies for effective classroom routines.
	- Formative 101: Building Routines <https://eml.newsela.com/NjI4LVpQRS01MTAAAAGbS69k_Bpm7tZs6qjsPX4_lUgUd-nFeNxCCFaUSxhqWAZU3WVKd_9iHF3d-Cp18-F0Z6nvGDs=>: New to Formative? Get practical tools to establish strong formative assessment habits from day one.

Subject: Thanks for applying to Gusto, Candace
Body Text:
Hi Candace,

Were excited to review your application for our Technical Program Manager opening!

We care deeply about attracting folks who care about our customers, and of course, our mission: to create a world where work empowers a better life. Were thrilled and grateful that youd like to join us on this journey.

Our Invite (a.k.a. Recruiting) team will take care of things from here and reach out with next steps. Please note that we are working diligently to review a high volume of applications and we sincerely appreciate your patience. In the meantime, sit back, relax, and check out a behind-the-scenes look ( https://gusto.com/company-news ) at life at Gusto to pass the time.

If you're wondering, here's a link to read more about our Privacy Policy ( https://gusto.com/about/privacy ).

With Gusto,
The Invite Team

Gusto | The people platform built for small businesses.

Subject: Message for empathetic people ONLY
Body Text:
If youre reading this email - then you have a rare talent, Candace...



 One that money cant buy.



 And teachers cant teach.



Most people cant imagine having your talent.



But they wish they did.



 Because you understand people in ways others can't.



 You see beneath the surface.



 In 2025, your empathy has become incredibly valuable.



Why?





Well, as more and more technology comes into our lives



People are craving REAL, human connections.



Studies have found that dating apps lead to less satisfied relationships.



And the rise in remote work is leaving people feeling lost and isolated.



More technology is not the answer.



You are.



You have the ability to genuinely connect with other people on a level technology cant.



To make them feel heard.



And give them human to human guidance that will change their life.
