Subject: You have successfully applied to Program Manager
Body Text:
Thank you for your application to the Program Managerposition with Experis! We appreciate your interest in joining our team.Here are the steps to get started:
Create and/or update your profile on experis.com: To begin your journey with Experis, please visit our website at experis.com and create a profile. If you already have an existing profile, we encourage you to update it with your latest qualifications and experiences. By creating a profile, you can save your searches, track your applications, and receive updates on new job openings that match your skills and preferences.
Explore IT-driven opportunities: Experis specializes in IT-driven opportunities, providing a wide range of career options in the technology industry. We have a diverse portfolio of clients seeking talented individuals like you. Browse our website to discover the latest IT job openings that match your skills and interests.
Stay in touch: Your journey with Experis has just begun. We have received your application and are currently reviewing your qualifications. If your profile aligns with our requirements for a specific IT role, a member of our recruiting team will reach out to you to discuss the next steps in the process.
In the meantime, we encourage you to explore the following resources to learn more about Experis and enhance your IT-driven career journey:
Join the Experis IT Community: Follow our Instagram, LinkedIn, and YouTube channels to stay updated on the latest IT job opportunities, industry trends, and insights.
At Experis, we are committed to providing challenging and rewarding IT-driven work in a collaborative team environment. We value our employees and offer comprehensive benefits to eligible candidates. As an industry leader, we are always seeking bright and talented individuals to contribute to our clients' success. We wish you every success in your IT job search with Experis.Warm Regards,Experis Recruiting TeamPlease note that this message is from an unmonitored mailbox, and we kindly request that you do not reply to it.

Subject: Let's Connect: Your Path to AI Agents Mastery Awaits
Body Text: Hi there,  I tried to contact you today to discuss the Agentic AI Pioneer Program but couldn't get through.  Your vision for staying ahead in the rapidly evolving AI Agents landscape is something we are excited to support. In the program you'll grasp both fundamental and advanced AI Agents through a dynamic mix of theory and hands-on experience.  What You Can Look Forward To: 	Expert Mentorship: Personal guidance from top professionals in the AI Agents field.	In-Depth Curriculum: Over 150 hours of detailed learning.	Tool Proficiency: Master over 15 leading AI Agents tools, libraries, and frameworks.	Real-World Projects : Engage in more than 50+ practical projects, equipping you for real industry challenges.  I believe a conversation could really highlight how this program aligns with your professional aspirations and enhances your skill set.  Would you be available for a call to explore this further? Please let me know a convenient time for you.  I've attached our program brochure for your review here . I eagerly await the opportunity to discuss how we can facilitate your journey into the world of Generative AI.  Warm regards, Ashutosh  +91-9911327650

Subject: The Secret to Writing Hooks That Keep Viewers Watching
Body Text:
Hey Candace,

Hope you're having a good day.

Its that time of year again for us - Quarterly Planning - and
this time, the team are all here with me in Hong Kong 

It's been a productive week and I'll be talking more about our
reflections in this week's issue of my personal newsletter,
LifeNotes, which you can join here (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/d0ugqd98lob0hokn8o8tmhz8vv544fl/7qh7h2u9k20lr0a9/aHR0cHM6Ly9hbGlhYmRhYWwuY29tL25ld3NsZXR0ZXIv
).

Anyway, I actually wanted to talk about an area of scripting and
video production thats still overlooked on YouTube - the hook.

The other day, I was scripting a Book Club video called Watch
This If You Feel Like Youre Behind in Life. Its about something
called mimetic desirewhich Luke Burgis talks about in his book
Wantingbut as I was working on the script for this video, I
found myself overthinking the hookagain 

And I do this a lot.

In fact, I sometimes write multiple different versions of the
hook before filming a video, and Ill often record these right at
the end of my filming session when Ive properly warmed up.

(Incidentally, this idea of filming the hook after youve
recorded was a hack I discovered last year after spending hours
trying to get a hook correct before actually getting the video
filmed - it genuinely works, would recommend).

Anyway, as youd have heard me or other creators talk about in
the past, the first 30 seconds of your video are the most
important part of the contentits when a viewer decides to
either stick around and keep watching or click away.

So if theres one thing worth obsessing over in your videos, its
the hook.

But writing a great hook can be tricky, so I wanted to share a
few essential (and optional) elements to take yours from a level
1 to a level 3 

 Essential Elements - The 3 Ps
-------------------------------

1 Promise

The first 5-10 seconds of your video should closely align with
the title and thumbnail. If your videos called The Secret to
Making Money on YouTube, dont open with a random story about
what you ate for breakfast that morning.

Instead, make sure that content you deliver immediately matches
the promise made in the title and thumbnail. For example you
could say, Most people fail at making money on YouTube because
they get one crucial thing wrong.

2 Proof

Give people a reason to trust you, because viewers are more
likely to stick around when they believe you know what youre
talking about. So if youre talking about growing a business,
share your experience as a successful entrepreneur.

Youll notice that I give a similar intro spiel at the start of
most of my videos, and it goes something along the lines of: Btw
if we havent met, hi my names Ali, Im a doctor turned
entrepreneur and author of the New York Times bestseller,
Feel-Good Productivity. Since 2017, Ive been making videos on
this channel about books, ideas, strategies and tools that help
build a life we love. These days, my main gig is building Sparkle
Studios, where my wife and I are creating a series of
productivity apps we wish existed in the world, like Voicepal (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/d0ugqd98lob0hokn8o8tmhz8vv544fl/owhkhwuwkm492rhq/aHR0cHM6Ly9nby5hbGlhYmRhYWwuY29tL3ZvaWNlcGFsL2NyZWF0b3Jub3Rlcw==
).

3 Plan

Give people a reason to keep watching by hinting at the main
payoffor the main value theyll get from the video.

Instead of saying, By the end of this video, youll know how to
stop procrastinating, you could create an open loop: Theres
one simple mindset shift that completely changed how I approach
productivityand most people get it wrong.

This creates a curiosity gap which is an important element in
encouraging people to keep watching.

 3 Optional Elements
---------------------

So those are the staple elements of a great video hook. But
remember, hooks dont need to be super long and complicated.

If you want to go even further, here are a few extra elements you
could consider including to make it even stronger:

1 Personal Anecdote  A quick personal story makes your hook
more relatable. So if youve struggled with the thing youre
teaching, definitely share that with your audience. It helps
people connect with you on a deeper level, and theyll be more
likely to stick around and subscribe.

2 Input Bias - People value content more when they know how
much time/effort/money went into it. For example, you could say
something like, I read 10 books on this topic so you dont have
to or I spent a whole week researching this idea, and this is
everything I learnt.

3 Target, Transformation, Stakes - This formula was created by
a guy called George Blackman. Fun fact: George started working as
a scriptwriter for me back in the day, and its a great framework
to use when writing your hooks (and hes actually coming to do
some scriptwriting sessions for the PTYA (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/d0ugqd98lob0hokn8o8tmhz8vv544fl/z2hgh7ue42o6qeuz/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYWxpYWJkYWFsLmNvbS9wYXJ0LXRpbWUteW91dHViZXItYWNhZGVteS8_dXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPWhvb2tzX2FwcjImdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPWNyZWF0b3Jub3Rlcw==
) community this year )

* Identify your target audience - Who is this video for? (E.g.,
If youre someone who struggles to find motivation)
* Share their desired transformation - What will they get out of
watching this video? (E.g., and you want to finally feel in
control of your time.).
* Highlight whats at stake - What will happen if they dont
watch this video? (E.g., you need to hear this, because
otherwise, youll stay stuck in the same cycle forever.).

As I share with my PTYA (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/d0ugqd98lob0hokn8o8tmhz8vv544fl/z2hgh7ue42o6qeuz/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYWxpYWJkYWFsLmNvbS9wYXJ0LXRpbWUteW91dHViZXItYWNhZGVteS8_dXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPWhvb2tzX2FwcjImdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPWNyZWF0b3Jub3Rlcw==
) students, the best way to get better at something is through
action. It sounds obvious I know, but improvement only comes as a
result of doing the thing, so youll only level up your YouTube
hooks if you actually practice writing more of them 

So next time you sit down to script a video, try spending a bit
of extra time on the hook. Use some of the elements from this
email, test out what works with your audience, and dont be
afraid to run tiny experiments.

And if you want to take things a step further, you can learn more
about hooks, scripting and different ways of structuring each
video through joining PTYA (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/d0ugqd98lob0hokn8o8tmhz8vv544fl/z2hgh7ue42o6qeuz/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYWxpYWJkYWFsLmNvbS9wYXJ0LXRpbWUteW91dHViZXItYWNhZGVteS8_dXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPWhvb2tzX2FwcjImdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPWNyZWF0b3Jub3Rlcw==
) where we dive deeper into all these areas.

Id also love to read the hook for any video youre currently
working on, so please hit reply and share it with me. 

Happy writing!

Ali xx

https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/d0ugqd98lob0hokn8o8tmhz8vv544fl/p8hehqu43w96ngsr/aHR0cHM6Ly9nby5wdHlhLmNvbS9wdHlhLWJsLWZvb3Rlcg==
).

Subject: A free membership webinar, a feedback request, and the pros and cons of video
Body Text:
Hi there, 
 There are a lot of great things happening in the Podia community these days! If you havent stopped by in a while, you might be missing out on conversions, learning opportunities, and insights like these: 
 - Podia Pro Brittany Hardy is hosting a free webinar about building the Marketing Club membership, including what worked, what flopped, and what moved the needle in her business. Event details and a signup link are in her post. 
- Andy Ziegler from the Business Navigator shared their Podia website and is asking for feedback. Take a look and share your suggestions in the comments. 
- And Estevan Carlos Benson kicked off this discussion of video content vs written content, which has gotten several thoughtful replies. Click through to share what youve learned from your experiences. 
 Community access is included free on all plans, so start your 30-day free trial today to join the conversation and make new creator friends! 
 



 
 [Image "Podia+Blogging+Blog+Post+Announcement+Images.png?expires=1759300074&signature=47affdc1f0a8659f5fd1bf391e7251219c763b58639b913de9e8b17c43d3dc23&req=dSUlEs19lIVbUfMW2XS%2FiejohRA%2BpC8QXmwAZdUOtBFgfqDNhKQ%3D%0A"] 
 



 
 See you in the community, 
 Spencer from Podia

Subject: Update on your candidacy from Dropbox
Body Text:
body, td {font-family: Arial, sans-serif;}

            

people-over-places

Hi Candace,

Thank you for your interest in the Senior Data Scientist position at Dropbox!

As a Virtual First ( virtualfirst.dropbox.com ) company, Dropboxs location strategy is focused on distributing our workforce globally. Unfortunately, we do not have the ability to hire for Senior Data Scientist in your location and are not able to move forward with your candidacy at this time.

If youre interested, click here ( https://jobs.dropbox.com/talent-community?utm_source=ghtemp&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=eoasignup ) to stay in touch and join our Talent Community. Well send periodic updates with new roles and opportunities as they become available (we promise, no spam!)

Thank you again for considering Dropbox, and we wish you the best of luck in your job search.

----------------------------------
Talent Acquisition Team at Dropbox

----------------------------------

Keep up with #LifeInsideDropbox on

Instagram ( https://www.instagram.com/lifeinsidedropbox/ )

Facebook ( https://www.facebook.com/lifeinsidedropbox )

LinkedIn ( https://www.linkedin.com/company/dropbox/ )

Body Text:
March 27 | 7-8 PM

                                                               Learning Analytics and Artificial Intelligence (Online), M.S.Ed.

VIRTUAL INFORMATION SESSION




MARCH


                                27                              




Thursday, March 27 | 7-8 PM (ET)
                                                               

                                Please join us for a virtual information session <https://apply.gse.upenn.edu/register/?id=3063e991-1a39-49d9-8b0a-b9f73762ccb4&utm_campaign=LAAI_Mar27&utm_medium=email&utm_source=invite> to learn about our Learning Analytics and Artificial Intelligence (Online) M.S.Ed. program.
                                                               

                                Discover insights into the program's curriculum, meet the instructors, and learn about admission requirements. This event is your opportunity to ask questions and find out how this program can help you achieve your educational and career goals.
                                                               

We hope to see you there!


RSVP <https://apply.gse.upenn.edu/register/?id=3063e991-1a39-49d9-8b0a-b9f73762ccb4&utm_campaign=LAAI_Mar27&utm_medium=email&utm_source=invite>
Whether we are researchers, teachers, administrators, or counselors, we are united in our mission to use the power of education to deliver new possibilities and drive more positive outcomes.





3700 Walnut Street
                              Philadelphia, PA 19104

Subject: Ask me your questions, Candace
Body Text:
Hey Candace,



I really appreciate you showing up and taking the time to read my emails every week.



But something tells me theres a roadblock in your way.



Somewhere you feel stuck on your coaching journey.



And its stopping you from moving forward.



Im here to help and I mean that genuinely.



Just hit reply to this email and let me know where you feel stuck, what question you need answered, or what doubts you have.



And Ill see if theres something I can share to help you get the clarity you need.

-Jay Shetty, Jay Shetty Certification School ( https://call.jayshettycoaching.com/?el=booking-email-reminder-163-3&utm_campaign=booking-be&utm_campaign_name=JSCS%3A+Prospects+Week+162-4.5&utm_content_name=Ask+me+your+questions%2C+Name&utm_medium_name=email_action&utm_source_name=customer.io )

MARCH


                                27                              




Thursday, March 27 | 7-8 PM (ET)

Subject: Are you ready, Candace?
Body Text:
Hey Candace,



Im looking for 10 caring people who



 Love listening to others



 Need a new way to serve



 Want to make TODAY the day they finally did something about it



By applying to join as one of my new students ( https://call.jayshettycoaching.com/?el=booking-email-are-you-ready-161-5&utm_campaign=booking-be&utm_campaign_name=JSCS%3A+Prospects+Week+161-5&utm_content_name=Are+you+ready%2C+Name%3F&utm_medium_name=email_action&utm_source_name=customer.io ) enrolling today



and starting your journey to become a certified life coach by July.



(no past experience needed)

Just like Carmen & Swarna did.



Theyre two of my past students who turned their love of helping others into a career path as a Jay Shetty certified coach through my school.



Heres what Carmen said about her experience:



Everybody in the school is so supportive.



And you really feel like you are with like-minded people that are going through the same journey as you are



It doesn't feel like it's just an online course. It really feels like a genuine community.

Subject: Thank you for applying to Datadog
Body Text:
Hi Candace,

Thank you for your interest in Datadog! We wanted to confirm that we have received your application for the Enablement Program Manager, Sales job.

Our recruiting team manually reviews every single candidates profile, and we receive a high volume of applications, so it may be a couple of weeks before we can get in touch with you regarding the next steps.

While you wait for an update, you can learn more about Datadog by visiting our Careers page ( https://www.datadoghq.com/careers/ ). You can also learn more about #datadoglife from our employees on LinkedIn ( https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/datadoglife/ ) and Instagram ( https://www.instagram.com/datadoghq/ ).

We will be in touch soon!

Kind regards,

The Datadog Recruiting Team

PS: If you've applied for multiple roles, you may hear back from us more than once.

Subject: There's Still Time: Start Class September 29!
Body Text:
800.226.7625 | fullsail.edu

There's Still Time: Start Class September 29!
The fall semester is alive and well at Full Sail!

See if you qualify for an Academic Advantage Scholarship of up to $15,000. https://www.fullsail.edu/scholarships/academic-advantage-scholarship

Fall Ahead: Start Classes in September!

Fall application deadlines come at you fast, but if you think the fall semester left you behind  think again. It's not too late to start a bachelor's degree this fall with Full Sail University. Our online and on-campus programs are engaging, actionable, and hands-on.

As a student, you'll have the chance to gain practical knowledge and experience that can help you kick start your career. Our film and television grads emerge ready for the real world, with the ability to effectively balance the creative aspects of world building and storytelling with the practical aspects of running a production.

There's still time to pursue your passion this fall with Full Sail University, but don't wait to enroll  classes start on September 29! If you have any questions, call 800.226.7625 to speak with our Admissions team. Financial aid is available for those who qualify.

OH MY GOSH, I LOVE 
By Mia Leimkuhler

Hello! Mia here, filling in for Emily today. Always a pleasure.

I often feel shy and awkward at parties, so Im grateful that my job makes such
an easy conversation starter. Tell people you work at New York Times Cooking and
theyll immediately ask you for recipe recommendations, cooking tips and what
Melissa Clark is like in person. (In that order: Start with our Weeknight 100
[https://nl.nytimes.com/f/newsletter/GRNmNXvlLkZPu8csIx2cFQ~~/AAAAARA~/4HvqWhRJfi1Hwl3IJ57lDf-YykoAFK1-cjNMi98BA9wVreRcMcJbC-3Gx5Pqvafw7opBiCK80LZ0cuet9FORZPzYoKUUi5jHd7EeWnQGYwvw8NqSPxhb8OwJ9YHMCepYmU9rFm9KqsDpYPmz9lJIDXkjOgeLrw8TLTF0MA9xVT48x55LkcXmAZVSjbqq-X7EMJ2CrQVHRr-uaNgrT7AzrYKF_RTyv_-ZnOaosMpd9jzCYwD6x3TU_Z_o9hODi28BipsAfDY6QSsvmYvPasuskGMgipCvvPdIsG22y_jV0_WKffrTimRCbzM9-pveSJNOGnw_znK5KR0Baqt00FQ_G8wBxo1l0dvkwoLYp_a6EmDVYSJcf1Sfxey3v4RfSutz]
; a bench scraper
[https://nl.nytimes.com/f/a/GCaVU1ytMCbLDuCbAqtPtQ~~/AAAAARA~/3VTi7afmEFtJ5VDZObuA10etDjXXzTvTiSH2NAOul2IG2KcDH-RCW6R8ziHExrKJ9MRC9SOxsXXcojbhJGwGAsqK10REToQU7DqU6-NKUrdDAAmb3FTpc_achkRzVUPuz7M1XSkvxoOW4pLb0m6Q91m9k_Qhh3TII_3sagc55aPTsretaxs3woYvJKs6p14Wmx7B1d1eAlMPraSwbDjcQCPzlEylf3P0WJnFoazGxISNXp_OmrF681GRC1s1CE0mWYELqFkP1JB_q7XXo4lst-9g7uZvMLuZsx4FGQXm4A7szQGAhO4WVJl6Xpcic6MJ8836aKoWOftqXe5Nli7sxNwGK_257Z1VjUwjnZZjDl-ej3jTrsXKe86i2eZJq-oW] 
will be your best friend; an angel among us.)

Theyll also volunteer their favorite NYT Cooking recipe, which always brings me
joy. I had someone corner me at a party to tell me how much he adores Hetty Lui
McKinnons sheet-pan pierogies with brussels sprouts and kimchi
[https://nl.nytimes.com/f/cooking/DADrr5IfAK3sINBJZ3oZhw~~/AAAAARA~/l6sWPy_9ovjDOSjKxOPuJtWCYw4V7W7DVQrjCNQ5UEtIC_vW9M4P6qmclRjGkwZuEf17fg3M0-yEeozRIP-rqrqo-aJEBmeHOrnYV83l0u9-0u7CmF1MRPOZEvhI69iyBMmoC441ppf2AwfpaHsKoiSdqe8S3z4bgZvbdLImGlI46-JdYvyLdA6XRvqmNOsCmHeTDxyO0aFF6adueX5Mwvzrpa-qOV1H1tu-Pcj1K76aFGF-6ePgG9-9MkGQOu3ERYIdrWp_gYM8PXqvWiCRcMz4nkkhT7b3zq3dkGODLidtedLhT5Db3zpSmKR32vNGmAx3E5j6AzSUg4_9aSmSxOcS2q-k-NxtUnOGkCyBGvfizpC5l4FxuH1ukeGGbR9-mtwoobj2dycO3YNMKFnrSf_IyB3z0Y8N3_NAKLFZ6OY~]
. Im pretty sure he used the words brilliant and life-changing, or at least
those were the sentiments conveyed by his wide eyes and upheld hands.

So todays weeknight quintet is a gathering of recipes that have been
enthusiastically recommended to me by other NYT Cooking cookers, with two that I
always trot out for that Any favorites? question. Enjoy!

Peach pound cake

recommended to me, and then made it again several times. Everything clicks in
this dish: the plump, cheesy (or potatoey) dumplings; the earthy-sweet sprouts;
the caramelized kimchi; the sharp sour cream. This recipe is the reason I now
keep a package of pierogies in my freezer at all times.

Whenever he visits me, my brother requests that pasta with the green sauce.
This is that pasta with the green sauce, a recipe by Joshua McFadden adapted by
Tejal Rao. The green part comes from a pound of blanched kale blended with
sizzled garlic; Ive used regular green kale instead of lacinato nearly every
time (because thats what my corner store carries) and it always turns out
wonderfully.

Are you tired of hot honey yet? Good, me neither. I love this simple, 30-minute
Ali Slagle supper and recommend it to anyone who needs a go-to chicken dish with
the vegetable element built in. Make it as spicy  or not spicy  as you like by
scaling the chile up or down, and play with your greens. I crave the slightly
bitter edge escarole provides, but you might prefer chard, mustard greens or
kale. This is one of those dinners that, with a glass of wine, feels almost too
nice for a weeknight.

And lets end where we started, on a sheet-pan stunner. Longtime readers know
and love this Eric Kim classic, and its a perfect Welcome to NYT Cooking
recipe: versatile, clever, delicious, easy. This is the recipe I suggest to
anyone who needs a good clean-out-the-fridge option. I cant think of a better
way to use up one sweet potato, an onion, some kale (or broccoli or green beans
or brussels sprouts) and leftover rice. (Ive tried it with all of those
vegetables, by the way. All great.)

Subject: coaching  mentoring
Body Text:
Hey Candace,



I just heard one of my students talking about how, before they joined my school, they thought coaching = mentoring.



But theyre actually very different.



Winston, one of my studentsfrom Ontario, Canada, found this out when he joined my school last year.



Hed built a lifetime of experience and knowledge in high-level and senior corporate roles.



And now he felt called to share with others in a more meaningful way.



He thought that meant coaching.



But what he discovered insidemy coaching Certification School ( https://pages.jayshettycoaching.com/ovsl-video-bau-e/?el=OVSL-email-not-mentoring-173-2&utm_campaign_name=JSCS%3A+Prospects+Week+173-2&utm_content_name=coaching+%E2%89%A0+mentoring&utm_medium_name=email_action&utm_source_name=customer.io )flipped his idea of coaching on its head.



You see



 Winston discovered thatlife coaching is NOT about teaching.



 Its about empowering others to find answers within themselves - not telling them how to live their life.



Before joining my school, he had no idea coaching could be used this way.



That it was NOT about how smart or successful you are.



Buthow well you apply specific life coaching techniquesthat help others open doors within themselves.

This perspective shift alongside his new life coaching skills helped Winstonserve his clients in a profound new way.



And also helped him serve himself - through self-reflection and self-auditing.



If you want to find out if you have what it takes to coach like this

Watch this short video ( https://pages.jayshettycoaching.com/ovsl-video-bau-e/?el=OVSL-email-not-mentoring-173-2&utm_campaign_name=JSCS%3A+Prospects+Week+173-2&utm_content_name=coaching+%E2%89%A0+mentoring&utm_medium_name=email_action&utm_source_name=customer.io )that walks you through what coaching is - and how to know if its the right next step for you.

-Jay Shetty, Jay Shetty Certification School ( https://pages.jayshettycoaching.com/ovsl-video-bau-e/?el=OVSL-email-not-mentoring-173-2&utm_campaign_name=JSCS%3A+Prospects+Week+173-2&utm_content_name=coaching+%E2%89%A0+mentoring&utm_medium_name=email_action&utm_source_name=customer.io )ENROLLMENT OPEN

Subject: Shocking true story of St. Patrick
Body Text:
Maewyn was just a boy when he was sold into slavery.



Captured by pirates and taken to Ireland.



Where he spent 6 years working hard labor on cold, muddy farms.



Till one night, he escaped.



Alone in the dark, he walked 200 miles to the coast.



Where he boarded a ship and - against all the odds - made it home to his family.



Now



This is where most stories would end.



But not Maewyns.



Because once he got home he realized he couldnt ignore what hed seen or let his suffering be for nothing.



So he returned to Ireland.



This time, not as a victim - but as a guide and helper for others.



Over the decades to come



Maewyn built schools and churches to help the poorest in Irish society live better lives.



Today



The world remembers Maewyn as Saint Patrick.





And Im sharing his story today not just because its Saint Patricks Day - but because a lot of people come to my Certification School with stories of struggle.



Hardships theyve overcome in their life.



And struggles they feel called to turn into positive change and transformation for others.



Or as one student put it: turning pain into purpose



If that sounds like something you feel called to do, Candace...

Body Text:

The datascience@berkeley Student Experience

Our Master of Information and Data Science (MIDS) degree program is delivered online, but it's not like any other online learning experience you've ever seen.

LEARN MORE
https://click.sfmc.datascience.berkeley.edu/?qs=a660c0151b75156ae052f45c02113f33d7084a6caf388d9a77be823eb47e269cd511234aba78703105db7d0f12f16e5ceca67906e132323848a2a672e0a217cc
 
LIVE CLASSES
Our state-of-the-art online platform features live classes, which are collaborative seminars driven by problem solving and discussion.
 
IMMERSIVE COURSE WORK
Course work  including video lectures, case studies, and quizzes  is designed by UC Berkeley faculty to be dynamic and engaging.
 
IMMERSION EXPERIENCE
On-campus immersions are offered twice a year and are custom crafted to deliver additional learning, networking, and community-building opportunities.

SOCIAL ENGAGEMENT
With our online learning platform, you can meet for study sessions, work on group projects, or even attend virtual happy hours with your classmates.
 
STUDENT SUPPORT
Your Admissions Counselor is available to help you through the application process and, if you are accepted and enroll, you will enjoy dedicated support during your studies.

EXPERIENCE datascience@berkeley HERE
https://click.sfmc.datascience.berkeley.edu/?qs=a660c0151b75156a4b4d8eea5003459cad16d669775e123ba5613ec9c5ccf37964b12f7fb6d8587fb317960e20d535657da65eaf0a0e5ac7cd83db809fbed66a
 
To learn more, contact your Admissions Counselor at 855-678-MIDS or admissions@datascience.berkeley.edu.

Have Questions During Your Application Process?
Our admissions team is ready to help. Take advantage of our regularly hosted webinars where you can gain insights on the admissions process, application requirements, or any questions you have about our online program. Subject: Start creating with your Full seat on Figma Professional
Body Text:
You have a Full seat on your teams Professional planwhich gives you access to
Figma Design, Dev Mode, FigJam, and Figma Slides.

Lets take a look at how you can use these powerful tools to connect your entire
workflow, from brainstorm to design to handoff.

More design tools
[https://static.figma.com/uploads/c27b7966c446e43ae741dc8b66e4261d09c0b926]https://www.figma.com/


BUILD BETTER TOGETHER WITH FIGMA DESIGN 
Create, prototype, and share in real time. Invite teammates
[https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/360039481034-invite-team-members] to
collaborate on designs, craft interactive prototypes
[https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/sections/360006534454-create-prototypes], and
publish design libraries
[https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/360041051154-guide-to-libraries-in-figma]
with components everyone can reuse.

Go to Figma  [https://www.figma.com/]


BRING CLARITY TO HANDOFFS WITH DEV MODE
Ensure your designs translate accurately into code. When you mark designs as
ready for dev
[https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/26781702258583-dev-mode-statuses-and-notifications#h_01j96t2mjrc6t23w0n77d20rgm],
complete with dynamic measurements and annotations
[https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/20774752502935-add-measurements-and-annotate-designs-in-dev-mode],
developers know exactly what to build and how to build it.

Explore Dev Mode  [https://www.figma.com/community/file/1234941143610339388]


BRAINSTORM TOGETHER IN FIGJAM
Invite the whole team to share, comment, and react to ideas in real time. Use
audio conversations for immediate feedback, and gather votes to guide
decisions.

Start a FigJam  [https://www.figma.com/jam]


CREATE PRESENTATIONS LIKE A PRO WITH FIGMA SLIDES
Build decks with the power of figma design. You can create up to five custom
slides templates to deliver on-brand presentations across projects.

Try Slides  [https://www.figma.com/slides/new]



Figma is a design platform for teams who build products together. Born on the
Web, Figma helps the entire product team create, test, and ship better designs,
faster.

Subject: Why Every Creator Needs a Heavy Project
Body Text:
Why I'm searching for a Heavy Creative Project



Hey friends,

Quick thing before we start - Im looking for a full-time Social
Media Manager to join our team in person in Hong Kong. If you
know someone who could be interested, Id love if you could
please send them this link (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/8ku2xgekvdtoh2penpqskhkdpp599a3/qvh8h8ud42gz4mhg/aHR0cHM6Ly9hbGlhYmRhYWwuY29tL2pvYnMvc29jaWFsLW1lZGlhLW1hbmFnZXIv
) 

Anyway, this week, I came across an absolutely brilliant Substack
post titled: Make Something Heavy (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/8ku2xgekvdtoh2penpqskhkdpp599a3/g3hnhwumlo7rl4t3/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud29ya2luZ3RoZW9yeXMuY29tL3AvbWFrZS1zb21ldGhpbmctaGVhdnk=
) by Anu Atluru. Ill do my best to sort-of summarise the post
and share my personal takeaway from it, but if any of this
resonates, Id definitely recommend reading the whole thing -
its a 3-minute read.

The post makes the point that in the online world (much like in
the physical world), we intuitively feel the weight of what we
create.

In the real world, we value heavy, solid wood furniture more than
the lightweight IKEA versions - theres something about the
heaviness of the thing that lends it some extra value.

Similarly, in the online world, theres light and heavy
stuff.

Light weight stuff = tweets, TikToks, Instagram posts, issues of
this email newsletter etc

Medium weight stuff = YouTube videos, long-form blog posts etc

Heavy weight stuff = Books, feature-length movies, TV series,
major symphonies etc

Anus key point is that we as creators crave creating the heavy
stuff. This is why every creator who starts off creating
lightweight stuff eventually starts to feel thats a bit
meaningless. Almost everyone then wants to work on something
heavy:

* Filmmakers dont just want to make YouTube videos about camera
settings and tutorials. They also want to make their own feature
film.
* Musicians dont just want to release singles on Spotify. They
dream of creating full-length concept albums.
* Educators dont just want to keep making YouTube videos about
the same topic. They want to write their own book.

Her argument is that the heavy thing feels much more meaningful
compared to the lightweight things. But also, interestingly, that
many lightweight things do not add up to a heavyweight thing.

No matter how many you stack, Tweets and TikToks dont add up to
something heavy. They dont solidify. At best, theyre a pile of
snowflakes, intricate yet ephemeral. Beautiful while theyre
here, gone before they hit the ground
With this email newsletter for example - Ive been writing this
every week (ish) for 7 years. I started it in April 2017, and
were now in April 2025. Absolutely bananas. But even though Ive
written like 5 books worth of text, it doesnt at all feel like
Ive written 5 books. Writing 7 years of ephemeral email
newsletter issues doesnt add up to a substantial heavy
project.

Anus post really resonated because recently Ive been feeling a
bit lethargic around making videos and content. The waxing and
waning creative inspiration to make videos is something Ive
become very familiar with over the years. But Anus post gave me
an idea Id never considered before: that creating only
lightweight things for too long feels a little meaningless.

No one wants to stay in light mode forever. Sooner or later,
everyone gravitates toward heavy modetoward making something
with weight. Your lifes work will be heavy. Finding the balance
of light and heavy is the game
I didnt feel this while working on my book. From 2020 to 2023,
while I had the Big Heavy Creative Project of Feel-Good
Productivity (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/8ku2xgekvdtoh2penpqskhkdpp599a3/9qhzhdud63k065iz/aHR0cHM6Ly9nby5mZWVsZ29vZHByb2R1Y3Rpdml0eS5jb20vYW1hem9u
) to work on, the project had a gravitational pull that drew me
in even on days where I didnt feel particularly inspired. I was
never questioning myself thinking, Why am I writing this book in
the first place? The work I was doing always felt meaningful. It
never felt pointless.

Thats what Id love to have for my YouTube channel as well. Im
not sure what format that looks like. Maybe it looks like working
towards some sort of wider series. Maybe it looks like working on
the next book (more details on that coming soon). But thanks to
Anus post, and a mini therapy session with my wife Izzy (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/8ku2xgekvdtoh2penpqskhkdpp599a3/3ohphdu329602ksp/aHR0cHM6Ly9pbnN0YWdyYW0uY29tL2l6enlzZWFsZXk=
), Ive realised that for me, having a Heavy Creative Project to
work towards is really important to maintain inspiration and
motivation in what can otherwise be an endless hamster wheel of
cool, this videos done? great, onto the next one.

Some more quotes from the piece to end:

Its not that most people cant make heavy things. Its that they
dont notice they arent. Lightness has its virtuesit pulls us
in, subtly, innocently, whispering, Just do things. The machine
rewards movement, so we keep going, collecting badges. One day,
we look up and realize weve been running in place.
And then you feel it: a quiet, gnawing hollowness that, for all
the making, nothing has truly been made. Why does it feel bad to
stop posting after weeks of consistency? Because the force of
your work instantly drops to zero. It was all motion, no
massmomentum without weight. 99% dopamine, near-zero serotonin,
and no trace of oxytocin.This is the contemporary creators
dilemmathe contemporary generations dilemma.

You dont feel like a true creator because you havent made
anything heavy, and deep down, you know light things dont count.
Your output is high, but your imprint is low. You ship, but you
do not build. You call yourself a creator, but what have you made
that could survive a month offline? A year? A decade? If you
stopped posting tomorrow, would anything remain? Creating for
24-hour cycles isnt freedom, leverage, or legacyits just
renting out your time.
If any of this resonates, Id really recommend reading the post (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/8ku2xgekvdtoh2penpqskhkdpp599a3/g3hnhwumlo7rl4t3/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud29ya2luZ3RoZW9yeXMuY29tL3AvbWFrZS1zb21ldGhpbmctaGVhdnk=
) - its wonderful.

Have a great week!

Ali xx

P.S. Do you mind taking 50 seconds to
answer a few questions (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/8ku2xgekvdtoh2penpqskhkdpp599a3/n2hohquvx5wmx4b0/aHR0cHM6Ly9hbGlhYmRhYWwuY29tL25ld3NsZXR0ZXItc2lnbi11cC10aGFuay15b3UvP3N1cnZleQ==
) so that I can send the most helpful content possible? Thanks in
advance 

Whenever you're ready, here are some other ways I can help you:

Subject: Is coaching future-proof?
Body Text:
Hey Candace,



If youre worried about losing your career to a robot



Not having the income you need to fulfill your dreams and give your family the security they need



Or just scared that everything youve worked for and that youre passionate about is going to be taken away from you.



Then todays coaching lesson from Viraj Oza is perfect for you.



CLICK HERE TO WATCH NOW. ( https://pages.jayshettycoaching.com/mentor-coaching-6/?el=mentor-video-viraj-email-162-3&utm_campaign_name=JSCS%3A+Prospects+Week+162-3&utm_content_name=Is+coaching+future-proof%3F&utm_medium_name=email_action&utm_source_name=customer.io )



In this 2 minute video youll find out:

* Why coaching is the perfect future-proof career to start in 2025
*
How you can use coaching skills to create a unique niche for yourself in uncertain times and make a real impact for people who need support
* #1 reason why people will always want human coaches (no matter how advanced AI gets)
Click here to watch todays lesson now. ( https://pages.jayshettycoaching.com/mentor-coaching-6/?el=mentor-video-viraj-email-162-3&utm_campaign_name=JSCS%3A+Prospects+Week+162-3&utm_content_name=Is+coaching+future-proof%3F&utm_medium_name=email_action&utm_source_name=customer.io )

Subject: A Solution to the Packaging Problem...?
Body Text:
Hey Candace,

Hope you enjoyed last weeks rather lengthy email about our
packaging process for the Stop Wasting Time - How to Change your
Life in 90 Days video.

Just as an update, weve currently got an A/B test running with
the following two thumbnails if youre interested 





Weve not been running it long enough to see anything conclusive
yet but Ill keep you posted.

A/B testing is one thing that I didnt really talk about last
week. It can be an incredibly powerful tool for your content and
your channel - but there's a caveat that Ill get to in a minute.

Were always running at least 10-20 A/B tests on the back
catalogue - theres just so much untapped potential in content
that mightve been poorly packaged or simply needs an update to
reflect the current brand and weve had some incredible results
from doing this in the past.

As I mentioned last week, we generally rely on thumbnailtest.com
(
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/d0ugqd98lob0hoon7zehmhz87o444sl/owhkhwuw3ov5gqfq/aHR0cDovL3RodW1ibmFpbHRlc3QuY29t
) to run these experiments. YouTube does have an A/B testing
feature but it only gives you access to one metric which isnt
overly helpful, and also doesnt allow you to test titles so we
generally stick to Thumbnail Test.

So A/B testing can be really beneficial but whats the caveat?

Well, A/B testing isnt something Id recommend to everyone. I do
think its something that most people can get value from but if
youre a beginner just starting out, its far more important to
concentrate on improving your initial packaging, your consistency
and the quality of your content than worry about trying to run
multiple A/B tests.

You also often need a slightly larger dataset to generate
meaningful conclusions from the tests which you just don't have
when starting out. Even for us, some of the tests are rejected
because we dont get enough data so bear that in mind too.

But that doesnt mean packaging isnt important, as I hopefully
have made clear over recent weeks 

As I mentioned last week, we dont even start scripting a video
until weve decided on what the title and thumbnail is going to
be ahead of time.

Having said all of that, I realise the process of actually
creating thumbnails is often a blocker for people and so I wanted
to let you know that weve recently launched a packaging product
(
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/d0ugqd98lob0hoon7zehmhz87o444sl/z2hgh7ue9wv0pmfz/aHR0cHM6Ly9hbGlhYmRhYWwuY29tL3ZpcmFsLXRodW1ibmFpbC1wYWNrLz91dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249cGFja2FnaW5nX3B0MyZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9Y3JlYXRvcm5vdGVz
) that might help you if youre struggling with thumbnails for
your own content.

It's called the Viral Thumbnail Template Pack (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/d0ugqd98lob0hoon7zehmhz87o444sl/z2hgh7ue9wv0pmfz/aHR0cHM6Ly9hbGlhYmRhYWwuY29tL3ZpcmFsLXRodW1ibmFpbC1wYWNrLz91dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249cGFja2FnaW5nX3B0MyZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9Y3JlYXRvcm5vdGVz
) and consists of over 30 different templates that weve used
successfully on my channel for years which you can take and
easily edit using Canva or Photoshop to improve the packaging and
performance of your own videos.

Essentially, I wanted to make it as easy as possible to create
quality looking thumbnails and ensure you dont fall into the
same last-minute-trap that I did when I was starting out.

The templates are intentionally designed to be customisable and
easy to use and were planning to add new ones when we strike
upon more formats that work for us on my channel.

Weve also added walkthroughs on how to customise them to fit
your content plus given you access to some bonus lessons from
PTYA which go deeper on the importance of thumbnails and
packaging.

If that sounds interesting, the packs $39 and you can get access
and more info here (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/d0ugqd98lob0hoon7zehmhz87o444sl/z2hgh7ue9wv0pmfz/aHR0cHM6Ly9hbGlhYmRhYWwuY29tL3ZpcmFsLXRodW1ibmFpbC1wYWNrLz91dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249cGFja2FnaW5nX3B0MyZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9Y3JlYXRvcm5vdGVz
).

If youre happy with your packaging already, thats totally fine
- Ill be back next week with some more YouTube-related insights
where I promise I wont be talking about packaging 

Have a great week

Ali x

 Want to start a YouTube channel? Go here (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/d0ugqd98lob0hoon7zehmhz87o444sl/p8hehqu4kx08gecr/aHR0cHM6Ly9nby5wdHlhLmNvbS9wdHlhLWJsLWZvb3Rlcg==
).

Subject: Feel called to become a coach?
Body Text:
Hey Candace,



If youve been waiting for the right moment to step into your purpose and help othersthis could be it.



Im opening the doors for a new cohort of students to join me and my expert team at the Jay Shetty Certification School  and Id love for you to be part of it. ( https://pages.jayshettycoaching.com/c2c-video-bau-e/?el=C2C-email-called-161-8&utm_campaign_name=JSCS%3A+Prospects+Week+161-8&utm_content_name=Feel+called+to+become+a+coach%3F&utm_medium_name=email_action&utm_source_name=customer.io )



Imagine looking back at this moment and saying, Thats when everything changed.



That was the year you stepped forward with courage.

That was when you chose growth over fear.

That was the beginning of your new chapter.



And if you start now, you could be coaching your first clients later this year.

Just imagine that for a second  actually living your purpose, not just thinking about it.



At the Jay Shetty Certification School ( https://pages.jayshettycoaching.com/c2c-video-bau-e/?el=C2C-email-called-161-8&utm_campaign_name=JSCS%3A+Prospects+Week+161-8&utm_content_name=Feel+called+to+become+a+coach%3F&utm_medium_name=email_action&utm_source_name=customer.io ), youll receive everything you need to grow into the coach youre meant to be:

*
A complete 4 month life coach program with guidance, training, and mentoring from an experienced coach.
* Video lessons with me on everything you need to know to grow into your new role as a coach.
* Coaching demos and behind-the-scenes recordings from my sessions with clients.
*
Coaching practice with real people. And the chance to get feedback from your mentor.
* Complete guide to my ABC Coaching Framework - the 9-step system to coach any client to achieve any goal.
* Monthly live Q&A sessions with me, where I answer your questions directly.
* A private global community of over 3,100+ people walking this journey with you.
* Video, audio, and text niche training resources.
* Coaching tools, guides, and templates for your coaching sessions.
* 12-month post-graduate support.
* Business Launchpad, where we show you how to start and grow your coaching practice with confidence.


And once you graduate?



Youll be a Jay Shetty Certified Coach  fully certified and ready to make an impact.



This is more than a school. Its a transformation.

And Id love to be a part of this next chapter of your life.



If your heart is telling you its time, listen to it.



Your future is waiting.



Click here to join my school today  ( https://pages.jayshettycoaching.com/c2c-video-bau-e/?el=C2C-email-called-161-8&utm_campaign_name=JSCS%3A+Prospects+Week+161-8&utm_content_name=Feel+called+to+become+a+coach%3F&utm_medium_name=email_action&utm_source_name=customer.io )

-Jay Shetty, Jay Shetty Certification School ( https://pages.jayshettycoaching.com/c2c-video-bau-e/?el=C2C-email-called-161-8&utm_campaign_name=JSCS%3A+Prospects+Week+161-8&utm_content_name=Feel+called+to+become+a+coach%3F&utm_medium_name=email_action&utm_source_name=customer.io )

Subject: Your job alert for: Scrum Master, Plano, Texas
coaching  mentoring
Body Text:
Hey Candace,



I just heard one of my students talking about how, before they joined my school, they thought coaching = mentoring.



But theyre actually very different.



Winston, one of my students from Ontario, Canada, found this out when he joined my school last year.



Hed built a lifetime of experience and knowledge in high-level and senior corporate roles.



And now he felt called to share with others in a more meaningful way.



He thought that meant coaching.



But what he discovered inside my coaching Certification School ( https://pages.jayshettycoaching.com/ovsl-video-bau-e/?el=OVSL-email-coaching-162-2&utm_campaign_name=JSCS%3A+Prospects+Week+162-2&utm_content_name=coaching+%E2%89%A0+mentoring&utm_medium_name=email_action&utm_source_name=customer.io ) flipped his idea of coaching on its head.



You see



 Winston discovered that life coaching is NOT about teaching.



 Its about empowering others to find answers within themselves - not telling them how to live their life.



Before joining my school, he had no idea coaching could be used this way.



That it was NOT about how smart or successful you are.



But how well you apply specific life coaching techniques that help others open doors within themselves.

This perspective shift alongside his new life coaching skills helped Winston serve his clients in a profound new way.



And also helped him serve himself - through self-reflection and self-auditing.



If you want to find out if you have what it takes to coach like this

Watch this short video ( https://pages.jayshettycoaching.com/ovsl-video-bau-e/?el=OVSL-email-coaching-162-2&utm_campaign_name=JSCS%3A+Prospects+Week+162-2&utm_content_name=coaching+%E2%89%A0+mentoring&utm_medium_name=email_action&utm_source_name=customer.io ) that walks you through what coaching is - and how to know if its the right next step for you.

-Jay Shetty, Jay Shetty Certification School ( https://pages.jayshettycoaching.com/ovsl-video-bau-e/?el=OVSL-email-coaching-162-2&utm_campaign_name=JSCS%3A+Prospects+Week+162-2&utm_content_name=coaching+%E2%89%A0+mentoring&utm_medium_name=email_action&utm_source_name=customer.io )

Subject: If youve been searching for something more... this might be it
Body Text:
Hey Candace,



What if the most meaningful career of your life

hasnt happened yet?



You dont need a fancy degree.

You dont need years of experience.

And you definitely dont need to have it all figured out.



You just need the desire to make a difference.



In this short video I created, Ill show you whats possible when you take your life experiences  all the challenges, growth, and wisdom youve gained...



And use them to help others as a certified life coach.

And you could be next.

 A recognized coaching certification



 Graduate as a coach in a few months

Subject: Subqueries in the WHERE clause
Body Text:
View this post on the web at https://jessramosdata.substack.com/p/subqueries-in-the-where-clause

Got BDE?
Hi BDEs!  
Hope youre having an amazing summer so far! Ive been busy traveling for conferences and focusing on video content, but Im COMMITTED to getting back into this newsletter weekly again 
A few updates before I get into subqueries 
I did my first keynote at Infoshare in Gdask, Poland  I spoke on Staying Human in a Data-Driven World and explored how data-driven decisions can have real human consequences when made without empathy. From layoffs and firings to opaque performance reviews, these choices dont just negatively affect individuals, they also shape company culture in lasting ways.
I went to Snowflake Summit as an Insider to get a sneak preview of all of their new data and AI announcements! It was so fun to hang with friends and partner with one of my favorite data companies 
Ill be at Vidcon next week so if youre going, say hi 
Im launching a data analytics roadmap soon so STAY TUNED 
If youre new here:
 Who Am I?
Im Jess Ramos, the founder of Big Data Energy and the creator of the BEST SQL course and community: Big SQL Energy. Check me out on socials: LinkedIn [ https://substack.com/redirect/d4592dd0-f676-47de-8741-ede162f36d97?j=eyJ1IjoiNTFkc2s3In0.TG_s5GaRal_EYLFDF-UYKHL5eEiDcX8TdL6-5nynlYA ], Instagram [ https://substack.com/redirect/7135a23a-5026-454d-8ef0-91c4a422f368?j=eyJ1IjoiNTFkc2s3In0.TG_s5GaRal_EYLFDF-UYKHL5eEiDcX8TdL6-5nynlYA ], YouTube [ https://substack.com/redirect/c203b75b-a701-4800-b73f-e5890961fb8b?j=eyJ1IjoiNTFkc2s3In0.TG_s5GaRal_EYLFDF-UYKHL5eEiDcX8TdL6-5nynlYA ], and TikTok [ https://substack.com/redirect/2eae0a04-3e26-4e77-aa15-ed2519e4789f?j=eyJ1IjoiNTFkc2s3In0.TG_s5GaRal_EYLFDF-UYKHL5eEiDcX8TdL6-5nynlYA ]. And of course subscribe to my newsletter [ https://substack.com/redirect/434a09e4-1765-4394-b8d6-1404af713e93?j=eyJ1IjoiNTFkc2s3In0.TG_s5GaRal_EYLFDF-UYKHL5eEiDcX8TdL6-5nynlYA ] here for all my upcoming lessons and updates all for free!
 Social Highlights:
Subqueries: The basics
Learning about subqueries goes along well with CTEs because almost every CTE can be written as a subquery and vice versa.
Subqueries are a query nested inside of another query. Technically you can have subqueries in subqueries in subqueries in subqueries and so on but dont do this to your coworkers LOL! They can also be turned inside out and written as a CTE (Ill show you an example of this later!) which greatly increases readability and interpretability. I highly recommend using CTEs for multiple nested subqueries or really complicated/long subqueries for better code organization and readability.
Subqueries vs. CTEs
A few differences between subqueries and CTEs are that:
Subqueries cannot be reused throughout the query unlike CTEs. CTEs can be referred to multiple times within the same query, but subqueries cannot be reused.
You dont have to name your subquery (although I recommend doing so with an alias) like you do a for CTE.
Subqueries cant be written recursively like CTEs. If youre not familiar with this, dont worry, its not used much!
Subqueries are generally harder to interpret since a reader has to start on the inside of the query and work their way out to understand it. I highly recommend using CTEs for more complex queries because too many subqueries can greatly decrease readability and ease of maintenance.
Subqueries in the WHERE clause
A really common example of a subquery is using it in the WHERE clause of the outer query. You use the subquery for conditional logic by using an operator and then filtering the original dataset for that condition. Check out this example below with an aggregate function, min( ):
select *
from orders
where 
   order_date = 
     (select min(order_date) from orders) --this is the subquery

-- you can also use other operators here, not just =
Here, the query is being filtered for all orders that have the minimum order date, which is the condition. They can also be used to filter for a column (or a list) in the where clause like this:
select *
from orders
where 
   order_id IN 
     (select order_id from payments) --this subquery produces 1 column
Here were selecting all the order IDs in the payments table and then filtering the orders table for those orders. This gives us all the orders data for the orders that are in the payments table. Why would we use this instead of manually adding in the IDs we want to search for like this?
select *
from orders
where 
   order_id IN 
     ('7364', '3820', '9818',...)
Imagine youre working with a HUGE dataset with thousands or millions of rows It wouldnt be convenient to type in or even copy and paste that many IDs into a query. Plus, you could even explode your IDE (not literally) by trying process all those!
Adding in a manual list requires you to figure out which ones to add ahead of time instead of them being added in automatically. This adds in an extra manual step into your process.
Perhaps the most important reason is that we dont want to hardcode in ID values unless its an ad hoc request thats never going to be used again. Its better to use a subquery here because the list will dynamically change and refresh every time you run the query. We love fresh data!
Subqueries are great for quick 1-liner queries to use conditional logic in the WHERE clause!
See yall next week!
Jess Ramos

Subject: Refresh Your Wardrobe - Shop SHEIN's Latest
Competition Launch: Image Matching 2025
Body Text:
Kaggle







Hi Candace Grant,

Finishing a puzzle can be hard enough, but what if pieces from otherpuzzles were mixed in, too? This makes the task even harder since you nowhave to find only the pieces you need. The same challenge applies tobuilding 3D scenes from real-world image sets, where unrelated photos arelumped together with relevant ones, complicating accurate scenereconstruction.

In this competition, you'll train a machine learning model to sort throughmixed image collections, group the right ones, and rebuild accurate 3Dscenes.





Total Prizes:

$50,000


Entry Deadline:

June 2, 2025




Learn More



Your work could improve how we use images in augmented reality, robotics,and even scientific research.

Good luck,

Sohier Dane
Kaggle Data Scientist



Kaggle, Inc 1600 Amphitheatre Pkwy Mountain View, CA 94043

   - Create programs with Python 3

   - Create data visualizations with Python matplotlib and seaborn
   - Summarize and analyze datasets
   - Conduct hypothesis testing
   - Clean and tidy datasets
   - Communicate your findings clearly
   - Run experiments and interpret the results

   models

   - Decide when to apply a given model
   - Conduct Feature Engineering
   - Leverage Jupyter Notebooks for experimentation and communication

Subject: GitHub Copilot: Whats in your free plan
Body Text:
Welcome to GitHub Copilot.
Heres how to get started.

You now have access to GitHub Copilot in VS Code and github.com for free as part of your GitHub user accountand
that includes support for models from OpenAI and Anthropic.

Ask Copilot how to get started >: https://github.com/copilot

Whats included

  - 2,000 intelligent code completions a month. Get context-aware code suggestions that draw context from your GitHub projects and VS Code workspace.
  - 50 Copilot Chat messages a month. Ask Copilot for help understanding code, refactoring something, or debugging an issue.
  - Choose your AI model. Pick between Claude 3.5 Sonnet or OpenAI GPT-4o.
  - Make changes to multiple files with Copilot Edits. Tackle changes across multiple files with Copilot Edits.
  - Support for the Copilot Extensions ecosystem. Access third-party agents designed for tasks such as querying Stack Overflow or searching the web with Perplexity.
  - Choose where you build. Enjoy support in VS Code and across GitHub.

So, what will you build?

P.S. - Not sure where to start? Try these Copilot Chat prompts >: https://docs.github.com/en/copilot/example-prompts-for-github-copilot-chat

Copilot Settings

GitHub Copilot will show code suggestions that match public code including code references in the VS Code and github.com experience: https://docs.github.com/en/copilot/using-github-copilot/finding-public-code-that-matches-github-copilot-suggestions

Subject: Are you joining, Candace?
Body Text:
Less than 72 hours left, Candace



Applications to join my next cohort of students ( https://call.jayshettycoaching.com/?el=booking-email-join-now-161-3&utm_campaign=booking-be&utm_campaign_name=JSCS%3A+Prospects+Week+161-3&utm_content_name=Are+you+joining%2C+Name%3F&utm_medium_name=email_action&utm_source_name=customer.io ) close this Friday.



By July, this group will be fully trained and ready to serve as Jay Shetty Certified Life Coaches.



But first



You have to apply for enrollment and complete an interview with my team.



This is where we:



 Understand where you are now - and why you want to become a coach



 Answer your questions about the school



 Make sure youre the right fit for us - and were the right fit for you



If your interview goes well



Youll be invited to join the next cohort. ( https://call.jayshettycoaching.com/?el=booking-email-join-now-161-3&utm_campaign=booking-be&utm_campaign_name=JSCS%3A+Prospects+Week+161-3&utm_content_name=Are+you+joining%2C+Name%3F&utm_medium_name=email_action&utm_source_name=customer.io )



And, between now and July, build the skills and experience you need to unlock:



 The freedom to help people every day (in a family-flexible career)



 The wisdom to create real transformation (on your own terms)



 The knowledge to grow personally and support those around you (even if youre starting with no past experience)



Like Anthony



Who shared this about his experience after graduating from my school:



Now I'm a full-time coach, I love what I do and I get to help transform people's lives.



It's just been such an awesome journey of building it from what was a side hustle to now into a full-time operation - and I couldn't be happier.



Now, its your turn.



You only have till 11:59pm EST on Friday to apply to enroll.



Lessons with my team are ready to begin.



If you feel called to coaching, this is your moment:



Click here to apply now and book your interview before enrollment closes on Friday. ( https://call.jayshettycoaching.com/?el=booking-email-join-now-161-3&utm_campaign=booking-be&utm_campaign_name=JSCS%3A+Prospects+Week+161-3&utm_content_name=Are+you+joining%2C+Name%3F&utm_medium_name=email_action&utm_source_name=customer.io )

Subject: Now Enrolling 2025 Students
Body Text:
Hey Candace,



Youve been part of my community for a long time



I couldnt ask for anything more.



You support me.



You watch my content.



You listen to my podcast.



Youre the reason I do what I do.



That being said, I have an exciting announcement that Id like to share with you.



I want to invite you to joinJay Shetty Certification School ( https://pages.jayshettycoaching.com/rewarding-career-video-bau-e/?el=RNC-email-rnow-enrolling-160-5&utm_campaign_name=JSCS%3A+Prospects+Week+160-5&utm_content_name=Now+Enrolling+2025+Students&utm_medium_name=email_action&utm_source_name=customer.io ).



Most people dont know that I have my own life coaching school.



Thats right. I train people every single day just like you to become professional Life Coaches.



Enrolling in this school is the perfect opportunity to:

* Learn new skills
*
Help others grow
* Find new purpose
* Make more money
* Begin a purposeful new career
*
And build community


Everyone who becomes a life coach goes through a profound journey.



Nobody is left unchanged.



Its a meaningful process of self-discovery, growth, and transformation.



And now its your turn.



If you take your self-growth seriously



If youre just as passionate about wisdom as I am



If you want to learn how you can better the world while bettering yourself in the process

Subject: Still waiting, Candace?
Body Text:
Youve been reading my emails for a while, Candace



Now were at the end of February



And youre still waiting.



Ive met so many aspiring coaches who kept waiting to get started too.



Not because they didnt want to.



But because they didnt feel ready yet.



They felt almost like they needed permission to follow their passion and become a coach.



All that time



Their best-self was bottled up inside them, waiting to get out and make their life so much happier.



And their would-be clients were waiting for them to take that step and come help them too.



I dont want that to be you.



Not anymore.



So, if youre tired of waiting and want to start your training NOW to become a coach

Hi Candace,

Good news, there are new notifications & updates waiting for you in your Real Python account. Heres what you may have missed:

Announcement
------------

--------------------------------------------------------------
12,168 Python Learners Reported the Same Problem. We Fixed It.
--------------------------------------------------------------

( https://realpython.com/workshops/python-for-beginners/?utm_source=notification_summary&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=2025-09-29 )

After surveying thousands of beginners, we discovered something troubling: Many can follow tutorials perfectly but freeze when facing a blank file.

Sound familiar?

Our new 8-week cohort course tackles this Builders Gap head-on. Instead of memorizing syntax, youll learn to think in code through live instruction with Stephen Gruppetta (PhD, Real Python Core Team).

Limited to 10 students per group. Direct feedback on your actual code. No TAs, no chatbots. Stephen himself guides you from zero to building real programs.

Course runs Oct 13Dec 5. Registration closes soon.

Subject: The No-One-Cares Mindset
Body Text:
One of the most freeing mental shifts you can make



Hey Candace,

Just a quick announcement before we start. Were going to be
running our next free quarterly webinar - The Spring Reset - on
Saturday 29th March (two weeks today!). Weve been running these
quarterly reflections for the past year and everyone always gets
a tonne of value and clarity from them. A big part of my LifeOS
philosophy is regularly reflecting and aligning on your vision
and your goals and these 90 day check-ins are the perfect
opportunity to reflect on the first 90 days of 2025. Its
completely free, open to everyone and you can register with one
click here (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/68umq689r0u8h5w5zlmfohp657kkkh9/qvhmvgkqf8ud7gxz9dtg/aHR0cHM6Ly9hbGlhYmRhYWwuY29tL3NwcmluZy1yZXNldC1jb25maXJtYXRpb24v
), look forward to seeing you there 

Ive been thinking a lot about a strategy that I (subconsciously)
used when I first started putting myself out there on the
internet.

I call it the No-One-Cares Mindset (NOC Mindset), and its one of
the most freeing mental shifts you can make.

Heres how it works:

1 When struggling to take action, ask: Whats actually stopping
me?

Is the task genuinely difficult? Or am I just afraid of what
people might think?

2 If fear of judgment is the reason, remind yourself: No one
actually cares.

3 Then ask: Whats the absolute worst that could happen if I
did this? And can I survive it?

Why This Works
--------------

Most of the time, we overestimate how much people are paying
attention.

In reality, everyone is busy living their own lives. Theyre not
sitting around critiquing your every move.

People are too caught up in their own problems, responsibilities,
and insecurities to spend much time thinking about what youre
doing. The few who do notice might have a fleeting opinion, but
within minutes, theyre back to worrying about themselves.

Think about it: how often do you spend time analysing someone
elses early attempts at something? Do you replay a strangers
awkward first YouTube video in your head weeks later? Do you
judge someone for launching a small business that didnt take
off? Probably not.

You might notice it for a second, but then you move on.

Thats exactly what happens when you put yourself out there.

Even if your first attempt isnt great, the reality is:

* Most people wont notice.
* The few who do will forget quickly.
* The ones who matter will respect you for trying.

For example:

 Starting a YouTube channel

No one cares if the first few videos are cringey. The worst that
happens? They get a few views, and you improve over time.

 Writing a blog

No one cares if the writing is a bit rambly. The worst that
happens? Only a handful of people (maybe just your mum) read it,
and you get better with practice.

 Starting a business

No one cares if your first few businesses fail. The worst that
happens? You learn, pivot, and try again.

And heres the kicker if you keep going, the people who
initially didnt care (or even doubted you) will eventually start
paying attention. Because consistency and progress are what get
noticed in the long run.

So instead of worrying about judgment, focus on doing the thing.

Because while you're hesitating, someone else is out there
trying, failing, learning, and getting better.

Have a great week!

Ali xx

Learning.

learned in this Career Path and can share these projects with your
community and future employers.

Once again, congratulations on finishing a challenging learning journey! We
hope that you continue to build on your skills for years to come.

Subject: We failed 78% of our goals. Heres why thats okay.
Body Text:
Q1 was a lesson in overcommitment: 18 goals set, only
4 completed. Heres how were rethinking focus and goal-setting
for Q2.



Hey friends,

This week, my team flew into Hong Kong for our quarterly offsite
 We pulled up the Notion doc from January where wed excitedly
mapped out 18 quests for Q1, and then checked what we actually
completed.

We finished 4. Just 4 out of 18. Thats a grand total of 22%.

Not great.

Quick sidebar - we call our goals quests because it just sounds
more fun and slightly less corporate. It adds a bit of a
Feel-Good vibe to what would otherwise be a dry planning
document. But still 4 out of 18 quests?

At first, it felt a bit embarrassing. We had such a clear plan.
What happened?

But then I remembered something from Traction (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/27u74ok3xrboh8gz52nh3hgl55w44hg/vqh3hmuoxw3k53tw/aHR0cHM6Ly9nZW5pLnVzL1A5blNxRW0=
) by Gino Wickman (honestly one of the most useful business books
Ive ever read). Apparently, when companies do structured
goal-setting for the first time, they typically only hit around
30% of their targets. Which, now that I think about it, makes us
almost average?

Still. It stings. But also, it makes total sense. The reason is
super simple: we all just set too many goals.

Especially when weve got a growing team. Its so tempting to
think: Well, weve got 18 people, so surely we can do 18
things. One quest per person. Perfectly logical, right?

Except, thats not really how it works.

More people doesnt mean more output. It means more coordination,
more communication, more updates, more ambiguity And that
translates into more meetings, more Slack threads, more Loom
videos to watch, and more decisions that need to be made before
anything actually ships.

Every new goal introduces a hidden tax: someone has to define it,
track it, push it forward, check in on progress, loop others in,
unblock issues and before you know it, half your time is spent
talking about work rather than doing the work.

This happens in my personal life, too. The more goals I set, the
less likely I am to complete any of them. I tell myself, Its
fine, Ill just work on these in parallel. But what ends up
happening is everything moves forward by 10%, and nothing ever
quite finishes.

The same principle shows up at the team level. When we took a
closer look at our Q1 quests, we realised that for most of them,
wed made decent progress. A lot of them were around 6080% done.
But as Traction puts it: 90% done is still not done. And once
we see that, its hard to unsee.

So this quarter, were changing the way we approach things.

Weve got three main departments (Content, Software, and
Courses), and in the spirit of boiling each departments progress
down to one measurable goal, we decided to go with the following
numbers:

* For Content: Grow the email list
* For Software: Increase monthly recurring revenue
* For Courses: Grow revenue

And under each of those goals, were only allowing ourselves up
to three major projects. No more trying to spin nine different
plates at once. Just three key things, scoped tightly enough that
we can actually finish them within the quarter.

Its surprisingly hard to do. There are so many exciting ideas
floating aroundproduct updates we could build, content
experiments we could try, partnerships we could explore. But this
new system forces us to ask: Of all the things we could do
whats the one thing that would move the needle most
meaningfully?

If were honest, we already know what the big levers are. The
hard part is committing to them. Saying no to all the other
shiny ideas that might feel urgent or important in the moment.

22% completion isnt something to be proud of. But I actually
think its a really valuable data point. Its a reminder that
its easy to get distracted by moving in many different
directions instead of focusing on what would make the most
meaningful progress to the business.

We even talk about it repeatedly in LifeOS (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/27u74ok3xrboh8gz52nh3hgl55w44hg/m2h7h6u3g40nrnhl/aHR0cHM6Ly9hbGlhYmRhYWwuY29tL2xpZmVvcz91dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249YXByaWw0JnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1saWZlbm90ZXM=
), including in the Spring Reset that we hosted last Saturday.
Funnily enough, we dont follow our own advice. Its a lesson we
keep having to relearn: the more goals we set, the less likely we
are to achieve any of them.

Have a great week!

Ali xx

Subject: 1 out of 1,000 - 20 criteria from heavy hitters
Body Text:
Here is how to be 1 out 1,000 from billionaires, pro athletes, centimillionaires, and family offices.Hi Candace,

To succeed and grow today, you need to be far more dialed in than just two years ago. To stand out in an inbox, you have to be 1 out of 1,000  but what does that really mean?

To me, it means you do what you said you'd do the first time. You present a compelling, unique offer. You hold a powerful position in your industry  and express it in a way no one else can because of what you've built (our efforts to do that are listed below my signature).

Being 1 in 1,000 also means you can enter extreme focus mode, add value first, acquire choke points, move with high velocity and high integrity, and structure creative agreements.

But who am I? A small business owner. I run an investor club. Youd probably rather hear what 1 in 1,000 means from a billionaire, pro athlete, $100M+ capital raiser, or ultra-wealthy investor. So here are their insights, pulled directly from our Investor Super Intelligence platform of AI tools:

**1) Billionaire Perspective** [Drawn from 1,000+ public billionaire talks from our Billionaire Collective Intelligence AI tool]

**Relentlessly pursue high-leverage priorities with elite energy, brutal self-awareness, and compounding judgment  while building systems that scale people, capital, and decisions faster than competitors can copy you.**

**2) Pro Athlete** [Using our AI tool on pro athletes]

**Become violently focused, ruthlessly disciplined, deeply self-aware, and execute faster than anyone elsewhile staying humble, healthy, and relentlessly valuable to others. Beast Mode Work Ethic: Outlearn and outwork everyone. Like Mike Tyson said, You dedicate your life to being the best. Say it. Believe it. Become it.**

**3) $100M+ Capital Raiser** [From our Coffee with $100M+ Capital Raisers AI Tool]:

**Relentless focus on your highest-leverage niche, paired with obsessive implementation speed, authentic positioning, and long-term relationship compoundingall while staying mentally and physically unbreakable.**

**4) Ultra-Wealthy Investor/Family Office** [From our Investor Advantage AI Tool with 4 million data points & 1,500 investor talks transcribed]

**Be obsessively focused on a narrow niche, build an unbreakable ethical reputation, make bold decisions faster than your competitors, and continually sharpen your strategic influence.**

**-----------------------**

Who wants to access our investor club's mobile app and watch all 1,500 hours of investor talks? Nobody, you are busy like everyone else.

Who wouldn't want to instantly be able to pull insights from 1,500 hours of investors talking on the .01% of things they care about right now?This is an example of that on this, for just one of the 100 questions that could be asked.

I hope you find these ideas helpful, and I look forward to seeing you at one of our monthly investor club events.

Richard C. Wilson

CEO & Founder

Team Help Line: (305) 677-3327

Family Office Club

New York City | Los Angeles | Fort Lauderdale | Dallas

**Tap into the $14 trillion family office market through the Family Office Club's 1,000 investors, 30 proprietary artificial intelligence Tools, and 16 live events**

-------------------------- 

Here are some additional billionaire insights on being 1 out of 1,000 

**🔥 5 Key Traits of 1-in-1,000 Founders (from billionaire transcripts):** * 

**Extreme Clarity on the Game Youre Playing**

* 

**Peter Thiel:** Dont just be the best at what you do  be the only one who does what you do.

* Know your power law: whats the 10x outcome, and what few moves will drive 90% of that?

* 

**Compounding Discipline + Judgment**

* 

**Jeff Bezos:** I always knew that if I failed I wouldn't regret that, but I knew the one thing I might regret is not trying.

* Create mental models (regret minimization, second-order thinking, etc.) to make repeatable high-leverage decisions.

* 

**Relentless Talent Upgrades**

* 

**Reed Hastings (Netflix):** Do not tolerate brilliant jerks. The cost to teamwork is too high.

* Build a recruiting engine. Hire slowly, fire quickly, and only promote missionaries  not mercenaries.

* 

**Time Mastery + Deep Work Systems**

* 

**Elon Musk:** You should take the most important thing you're working on and ask: how can I make this go faster?

* Ruthlessly audit your calendar and energy use. Turn time into throughput. Stack focus blocks daily.

* 

**Unshakeable Vision + Adaptive Execution**

* 

**Sarah Blakely (Spanx):** Mindset is the single greatest asset an entrepreneur has. Work on it daily.

* Drive your mission with conviction  but test, iterate, and evolve how you deliver it. Stay flexible in tactics, rigid in vision.

Sent to: aicoaching2025@gmail.com

Absolutely! And we stand by that.

But heres the ceiling you hit when you ONLY sell services:

Youre still trading hours for dollarsand the brutal truth is

Subject: Competition Launch: FGVC12 2025
Body Text:
Kaggle







Hi Candace Grant,

Put your computer vision skills to the test with this series of researchcompetitions that focus on fine-grained categorization - differentiatingbetween plant or animal species, for example - that pushes the limits ofboth human and machine performance. You can find these competitions on ournew community spotlight shelf on our main page.

Help advance image categorization research when you classify marine animalsinto taxonomic categories, identify plants using quadrat images, orre-identify animals based on unique traits, among others.





We are excited to host the competitions supporting the Fine-Grained VisualCategorization (FGVC12) workshop at the 2025 Computer Vision and PatternRecognition Conference (CVPR 2025) in Nashville, the foremost computervision event of the year.


AnimalCLEF25 @ CVPR-FGVC & LifeCLEF
FungiCLEF25 @ CVPR-FGVC & LifeCLEF
PlantCLEF2025 @ LifeCLEF & CVPR-FGVC
GeoLifeCLEF25 @ CVPR & LifeCLEF
FathomNet 2025 @ CVPR-FGVC


Participate in one or all of the FGVC Competitions to expand the field ofcomputer vision.

Good luck,

Maggie Demkin
Kaggle Competitions



Kaggle, Inc 1600 Amphitheatre Pkwy Mountain View, CA 94043

Subject: #1 myth about coaching
Body Text:
Alan did everything right on paper.



 Engineering degree.

 Corporate career.

 Boardroom access.

 Promotions.



But behind the success



Something was missing.



He kept seeing leaders who were smart - but not in tune.



Ambitious - but out of alignment.



And one day he realized that he didn't want to climb higher up the corporate ladder.



He wanted to go deeper.



He didn't just want to lead people.



He wanted to serve them...

* With clarity.
*
With emotional wisdom.
* With coaching skills that create real transformation.


That's what led him to my Certification School.



Not just to learn how to coach - but to become the kind of leader he never had.



Since completing the program



Alan feels hes taken a huge step towards becoming the leader he always dreamed of being.



And he now coaches others on how to lead themselves first, so they can lead others better.





If you've ever felt called to lead differently



To coach and guide others in a way you see is missing in the world right now



Then this video ( https://pages.jayshettycoaching.com/ovsl-video-bau-e/?el=OVSL-email-holistic-leader-173-1&utm_campaign_name=JSCS%3A+Prospects+Week+173-1&utm_content_name=Become+a+holistic+leader+%28and+coach%29&utm_medium_name=email_action&utm_source_name=customer.io ) is for you.

Subject: [Day 5 Assignments] 5-Day Gen AI Intensive
Body Text:
Kaggle


Hello Candace,

We've reached the last day's assignment! 

 Final Assignment

Complete Unit 5 - MLOps for Generative AI:


Listen to the summary podcast episode for this unit.
To complement the podcast, read the MLOps for Generative AI whitepaper.
No codelab for today! During the livestream tomorrow, we will do a codewalkthrough and live demo of goo.gle/agent-starter-pack, a resource createdfor making MLOps for Gen AI easier and accelerating the path to production.Please go through the repository in advance.
Want to have an interactive conversation? Try adding the whitepaper toNotebookLM.

 What You'll Learn

Discover how to adapt MLOps practices for Generative AI and leverage VertexAI's tools for foundation models and generative AI applications such asAgentOps for agentic applications.

 Reminders and Announcements


Find the complete list of scheduled livestreams and past recordings here.

The final livestream is tomorrow at 11 AM PT / 7 PM CET / 11:30 PM ISThosted by Paige Bailey with special guests: Sokratis Kartakis, GabrielaHernandez Larios, Ivan Nardini, Anant Nawalgaria, Elia Secchi, MichaelStyer and Saurabh Tiwary.
Be sure to ask all your questions about the podcast and readings in the#5dgai-questions-2 channel on Discord.

Happy learning and see you tomorrow!

The Kaggle Team








Google

 2025 Kaggle, Inc 1600 Amphitheatre Pkwy Mountain View, CA 94043
